(87, 37, 'A guide to smart locks', NULL, 'What are the advantages of smart locks?', 'A smart door lock is a door lock which has built-in smart capabilities to allow for remote access and control over your front door. Smart door locks offer a wide range of benefits that have made them a popular addition to smart homes across the world.\r\n\r\nOf course, many people are still not 100% convinced on whether investing in a smart door lock is right for them. But it’s worth understanding their key benefits to work out if introducing one could be beneficial to you and your family.\r\n\r\n1. Smart but simple\r\nAs we’ve already highlighted, adding a smart lock to your home is a great way to make your front door security just that little bit easier and convenient. And although they’re generally referred to as ‘smart’ locks, they’ve been designed to make securing your home much simpler.\r\n\r\nThey allow homeowners to easily grant entry, safely and securely, to anyone who needs to get into their home whilst they’re out and about, which is much easier than giving them a spare key and collecting it when they’re back. This simplicity is revolutionary and can save you time and provide the ultimate flexibility in how you secure your home.\r\n\r\n2. Tailored to you\r\nFrom a key card to a key fob and, of course, your smartphone - a smart door lock allows you to choose the best way of opening your door and configure your locking system to suit you.\r\n\r\nFor example, for children who don’t yet own a smartphone, they can have a key fob on a keyring to securely get into the home after school. And if they lose it? Well, this can easily be removed from your system to ensure the ultimate protection if it was to get into the wrong hands.\r\n\r\nHaving the ability to opt for the best entry accessory is a great advantage that other traditional door locking systems could never provide.\r\n\r\n3. Stylish designs\r\nA door lock isn’t the most stylish accessory in your home, but smart locks have introduced a modern alternative where style is at the forefront of their design.\r\n\r\nWith an array of options on the market today, you can opt for a smart door lock that suits your home’s aesthetic - whether that be modern, traditional or colourful.\r\n\r\nFrom a contemporary white shade for a monochromatic home, to a brass finish for classic properties, there’s a finish available to achieve your desired look.\r\n\r\nThere’s also an array of options to suit different door types, whether that be UPVC, composite or wooden designs, so there will be a perfect product to best suit your door.\r\n\r\n4. No slack on security\r\nAnd, most importantly, opting for high quality smart locks, particular those from trusted brands such as Yale, means that their door locks will offer a high level of security matched to that of traditional door locks.\r\n\r\nOne particular way in which smart locks can even heighten your security is that it removes the need for spare keys. These can often go missing, be kept accidently by previous homeowners, or even get stolen, meaning they could be left in the wrong hands. As smart locks don’t have physical keys, this removes this worry immediately. You can grant and revoke keys with just the touch of a button, offering complete control over who has access to your home.\r\n\r\nWhen considering purchasing a smart lock, it’s important to recognise the brand in which you are purchasing from, as this can make a huge difference to the security of your door. Opting for a trusted brand, such as Yale, means you have the experience needed for a secure smart locking mechanism, so you can have peace of mind that your door is protected by the experts.', '1680329577.png', '', NULL, NULL, 'February 03, 2022', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-08-07 07:48:04', '2023-04-01 00:42:57'),
