(56, 36, 10, 'Check out and proceed to airport/ railway station and we wish you a pleasant return journey.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(55, 36, 9, 'After breakfast proceeds to Athirapally, Vazhachal waterfalls and Ezhattumukham take a deep bath and refresh your mind. Return back to the hotel and overnight stay at Kochi.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(54, 36, 8, 'Cochin – Munnar (130kms/4Hrs)\r\nAfter breakfast and check out proceeds for Rajamalai (Eravikulam) National Park – famous for Nilgiri Tahr (Wild goat), Anaimudi Peak – South India’s Highest Peak, Tata Tea Museum, evening proceed to Kochi. Overnight stay at Kochi.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(53, 36, 7, 'Thekkady – Munnar (85kms-4Hrs)\r\nCheck out and proceed to Munnar, on the way you can enjoy a lot of sightseeing and the journey through mountains and forest. Check in to the resort and evening sightseeing to \r\nKundala dam, eco point & Munnar town.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(52, 36, 6, 'After breakfast, take a boat ride to Periyar wildlife sanctuary and enjoy the wildlife.\r\nThe afternoon takes a jeep trekking to off-road safari.Overnight stay at Thekkady', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(51, 36, 5, 'Trivandrum - Thekkady (200 km 6 Hrs) \r\nCheck out and proceed to Thekkady, check in to the resort and enjoy the ambiance of the stay.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(50, 36, 4, 'Varkala – Trivandrum (45 km 1.30 Hrs) \r\nCheck out and proceed to Trivandrum and enjoy the sightseeing \r\n* Napier Museum\r\n* Pathmanabha swami Temple\r\n* Kuthira Malika\r\n* Kawadiyar palace\r\nCheck in to Kovalam and Overnight stay at Kovalam Enjoy the beach and sand', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(49, 36, 3, 'Alappuzha – Varkala (110km - 3. Hrs)\r\nAfter check-out proceeds to Varkala and check in to the hotel and enjoy the beach and sand with sunbath.', '2019-11-17 06:57:38', '2019-11-17 11:57:38'),
(57, 37, 1, 'Cochin –Munnar ( 153 km 4 hours)\r\nArrive Cochin airport/railway station, greetings and airport assistance, Transfer to Munnar. Munnar, the picturesque hill stations in India is situated at the confluence of three mountain streams - Mudrapuzha, Nallathanni, and Kundala. Sprawling tea plantations, picture book towns, winding lanes, trekking and holiday facilities make this destination a popular resort town. Munnar is home of Nilgiri Tahrs, an endangered species of wild goat. On arrival, check in to the hotel with the rest of the day to spend as you please- either relaxing or exploring tea city. Overnight at the at Hotel/Resort in Munnar.', '2018-11-02 12:59:53', '2018-11-02 16:59:53'),
(58, 37, 2, 'Munnar Breathtakingly Beautiful..\r\nA Haven of Peace and Tranquility.The idyllic Tourist Destination in God\'s own country. Set at an altitude of 6000 ft in Idukki district, Munnar was the favored summer resort of the erstwhile British rulers in the colonial days. Unending expanse of tea plantations - pristine valleys and mountains- exotic species of flora and fauna in its wild sanctuaries and forests - aroma of spice scented cool air. Overnight stay in Munnar\r\n•	Rajamala- Eravikulam National Park\r\n•	Mattupetty Dam\r\n•	Eco Point \r\n•	Tea plantation', '2018-11-02 12:59:53', '2018-11-02 16:59:53'),
(59, 37, 3, 'Day 3 Munnar to Thekkady (85 km 3 hours)\r\nCheck out and proceed to Thekkady. After check in to the resort enjoy the premises afternoon proceeds to jeep trekking and enjoy the wildlife. Overnight stay in Thekkady.\r\n•	4 hour off road drive inside the forest.', '2018-11-02 12:59:53', '2018-11-02 16:59:53'),
(60, 37, 4, 'After fresh up and breakfast proceed to Periyar wildlife sanctuary. Take a boat and enjoy the beauty of nature.', '2018-11-02 12:59:53', '2018-11-02 16:59:53'),
(61, 37, 5, 'Thekkady – Cochin (190km- 6 hours)\r\n Check out from the hotel and proceed to Cochin on the way you can enjoy the beauty spots like\r\n•	Kuttikanam\r\n•	Peerumedu\r\n•	Parunthum para\r\nEvening reach at Cochin, drop at airport/Railway station', '2018-11-02 12:59:53', '2018-11-02 16:59:53'),
(62, 38, 1, 'Cochin – Munnar (130kms/4Hrs)\r\nOn arrival in Cochin Airport/Railway station our cab will pick you up & proceed to Munnar, on the way enjoy the beauty of the waterfall, tea gardens Later check in to the hotel, in evening visit local market overnight accommodation at the hotel.', '2018-11-02 14:48:42', '2018-11-02 18:48:42'),
(63, 38, 2, 'After breakfast proceed for a romantic day in Munnar, visit the beautiful sightseeing spots like \r\n•	Rajamalai (Eravikulam) National Park.famous for Nilgiri Tahr (Wild goat), Anaimudi Peak – \r\n        South India’s Highest Peak,\r\n•	Tata Tea Museum \r\n•	Historical Church \r\n•	Mattupetty dam\r\n•	Echo Point\r\n•	Kundala Lake\r\n•	Spice Plantation\r\nOvernight stay at a hotel in Munnar', '2018-11-02 14:48:42', '2018-11-02 18:48:42'),
(64, 38, 3, 'Munnar – Thekkady (90kms/3Hrs)\r\nAfter breakfast proceeds to Thekkady, the charismatic hill station which situated in the banks of Periyar. One of the exotic Wildlife destination of Kerala. It’s also known as the spice bag of the state. You can enjoy a beautiful journey through the hills and valleys of Western Ghat to reach this jungle destination.also you can enjoy the misty route with a cool climate. \r\nCheck in your hotel and later go for Spice plantation visit, elephant ride, or an Ayurvedic massage treatment there. Also, have an amazing boat ride in Periyar Lake which flows through the Periyar tiger reserve. You will have a chance to watch the wild animals like elephant, Bison, Sambar, Deer etc. are roaming both shores, Rest of the day at disposal to explore the surroundings by owns. \r\nOvernight stay at the hotel in Thekkady.', '2018-11-02 14:48:42', '2018-11-02 18:48:42'),
(65, 38, 4, 'After breakfast, drive to Thekkady. The very sound of the word Thekkady conjures up images of elephants, unending chains of hills and spice scented plantations. In the Periyar forest of Thekkady is one of the finest wildlife reserves in India, and spread across the entire district are picturesque plantations and hill towns that hold great opportunities for treks and mountain walks. Evening enjoys the boating at the Periyar lake. Overnight stay at the resort in Thekkady.', '2018-11-02 14:48:42', '2018-11-02 18:48:42'),
(66, 38, 5, 'Thekkady – Alleppey (150kms/5Hrs)\r\nAfter Breakfast check out from the hotel. Proceed to Alleppey Arrive at Alleppey ready for the thrilling experience on the backwaters of Kerala. On this leisurely cruise, you will enjoy beautiful villages, paddy fields, small churches, temples and witness the day-to-day life of the villagers. Overnight at the Hotel.', '2018-11-02 14:48:42', '2018-11-02 18:48:42'),
