(94, 66, 1, 'On arrival at Trivandrum airport/railway station, you will be meeting our assistant waiting for you, later you will be driven to Kovalam. On arrival at Kovalam, you can check-in at the hotel and rest. Later you will be taken to visit the beautiful golden beaches of Kovalam like Lighthouse Beach, Howah Beach and Ashoka Beach. Overnight stay at the hotel in Kovalam.', '2018-11-02 15:40:52', '2018-11-02 19:40:52'),
(95, 66, 2, 'KOVALAM – TRIVANDRUM \r\nAfter breakfast at the hotel, you will proceed for an excursion in Trivandrum. On reaching, you will be taken for sightseeing to places like \r\nSree Padmanabha Swami Temple, \r\nKuthiramalika Palace Museum, \r\nThe Napier Museum, \r\nSree Chithra Art Gallery, \r\nZoological Park, \r\nScience & Technology Museum, \r\nKanakakunnu Palace,\r\nShanku Mukham beach.\r\nAfter Trivandrum sightseeing tour, you will return to Kovalam for an overnight stay at the hotel.', '2018-11-02 15:40:52', '2018-11-02 19:40:52'),
(96, 66, 3, 'KOVALAM – KANYAKUMARI (100km- 2.30 hours)\r\nAfter breakfast, you will be driven to Kanyakumari. On arrival, you can check-in at the selected hotel. Later, you can proceed for sightseeing tour of Kanyakumari and the sites you will visit are Kanyakumari Beach, Sangam (Confluence of Indian Ocean, Bay of Bengal and the Arabian Sea) and Vivekananda Rock. In the evening, you can view the beautiful sunset followed by an overnight stay in the hotel in Kanyakumari', '2018-11-02 15:40:52', '2018-11-02 19:40:52'),
(97, 66, 4, 'KANYAKUMARI – TRIVANDRUM DEPARTURE\r\nThe next day, you will be woken up early in the morning to revisit the sunrise in Kanyakumari. After breakfast, you will be driven to Trivandrum airport to connect flight for your onward destination.', '2018-11-02 15:40:52', '2018-11-02 19:40:52'),
(98, 67, 1, 'Coimbatore - Ooty (90km - 3 hours)\r\nOnce you arrive at Coimbatore you’ll be well assisted by our executive from where you will proceed to Ooty, the famed \"Queen of Hills\" in the Nilgiris of South India. Upon your arrival in Ooty, you’ll be checked into the hotel for overnight stay.\r\nght stay.', '2018-11-01 10:13:26', '2018-11-01 14:13:26'),
(99, 67, 2, 'A new day begins packed with scrummy breakfast after which you head to Ooty Railway Station to relish the serene view through the joyous toy train ride from Ooty to Coonoor  As you reach Coonoor you can pave your way to sight the Lamb Rock, Dolphin\'s Nose and later on get back to Ooty and on the way visit Rose garden, Botanical garden & Ooty Lake. Overnight stay in Ooty.', '2018-11-01 10:13:26', '2018-11-01 14:13:26'),
(100, 67, 3, 'Ooty -  Coimbatore -Kovai Kutralam Waterfalls140km 5hours)\r\nCheck out and proceed to Isha Foundation and Kovai Kutralam waterfalls.', '2018-11-01 10:13:26', '2018-11-01 14:13:26'),
(244, 99, 1, 'Night 01: Wednesday, 26 \r\nMeet at 16:30 Hrs at Atlas Airport hotel, Nedumbassery, for pre-Departure meeting, after the pre-departure meeting, drop at Cochin International Airport, Check-in at Silk Air Counter and after all Immigration process, ready to fly to Kuala Lumpur Via Singapore.\r\n\r\nMI 463 Cochin Departure 21:20 Hrs, Overnight at Flight\r\n\r\nDay 01 Thursday, 27 – December – 2018\r\n\r\nReached Singapore at 04:30 Hrs, finishing all security clearance from Singapore and ready to fly Kuala Lumpur.\r\n\r\nMI 322 Singapore departure 07:10 Hrs,\r\n\r\nArrive Kuala Lumpur at 08:05 Hrs. After finishing all immigration & customs clearance from Kuala Lumpur International Airport, Time to fresh up from International Airport (One Hour). Delicious buffet breakfast at an Indian restaurant is waiting for you. Then we proceed to Putrajaya & Cyberjaya Tour.\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, pick up from the hotel lobby and transfer to breathtaking scenery, lush green hills and beautiful landscape, by a cable car ride to Genting Highland with en route to Batu Caves. Batu Caves is an iconic and popular tourist attraction in Selangor. The site of a Hindu temple and shrine, Batu Caves attracts thousands of worshippers and tourists, especially during the annual Hindu festival, Thaipusam.\r\n\r\nA limestone outcrop located just north of Kuala Lumpur, Batu Caves has three main caves featuring temples and Hindu shrines. Its main attraction is the large statue of the Hindu God at the entrance, besides a steep 272 climb up its steps to finally view the stunning skyline of the city center. Monkeys frolic around the caves, and it is a popular spot for rock climbing enthusiasts. Paintings and scenes of Hindu Gods can also be seen in the Ramayana Cave. Arrive Genting and proceed to Casinos the Asia’s Largest Casino Centre with formal Dress with shoes (Gents) or by Malaysian traditional Dress.\r\n\r\nBuffet Lunch at Coffee Terrace Genting.\r\nBuffet Dinner at Coffee Terrace, Overnight stay at Hotel, First World – Genting Highlands.', '2018-11-15 10:16:12', '2018-11-15 15:16:12'),
(101, 67, 4, 'Coimbatore - Kodaikanal (180 km 5 hrs)\r\nEarly morning check out and proceed to Kodaikanal and Reach there at noon after Check-in and lunch proceed to the lake for sightseeing.', '2018-11-01 10:13:26', '2018-11-01 14:13:26'),
(102, 67, 5, 'Check out and Proceed to Kodaikanal sightseeing \r\nGuna cave,\r\nCoaker\'s Walk\r\nEcho Point\r\nSuicide point \r\nEvening proceeds to Coimbatore and drops at the hotel or transferring point.', '2018-11-01 10:13:26', '2018-11-01 14:13:26'),
(103, 68, 1, 'ARRIVAL AT JAIPUR\r\nUpon arrival at Delhi airport, meet Tour My India representatives, who will transfer you to the hotel. After relaxing in the hotel for a while, visit the famous attractions of Jaipur like Nahargarh Fort, and Birla Temple. In the evening, you can either explore the market or visit Chokhi Dhani at your own expense. After exploring the city, go back to the hotel for overnight stay.', '2018-11-17 14:45:30', '2018-11-17 19:45:30'),
(104, 68, 2, 'JAIPUR CITY TOUR\r\nToday, after breakfast, you will again go for Jaipur sightseeing tour. First, visit the Amber Fort where you will enjoy the safari. After exploring Amber fort, visit the Kanak Vrindavan Temple, and Hawa Mahal. After lunch, go to City Palace, Jantar Mantar, Jal Mahal, and Hawa Mahal. The evening will be free for leisure. Overnight stay at the Jaipur hotel.', '2018-11-17 14:45:30', '2018-11-17 19:45:30'),
(105, 68, 3, 'DEPARTURE\r\nCheck out from the hotel. You will be transferred to the airport or railway station for the journey onwards.', '2018-11-17 14:45:30', '2018-11-17 19:45:30'),
(106, 69, 1, 'Arrival at Delhi\r\nAs soon as you land at New Delhi Airport, our escort shall take you to the hotel. With a warm welcome at the hotel; we shall assist you with check-in. This Day is at leisure and you can enjoy the facilities of the hotel. Dinner and night stay shall be in the hotel itself.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(107, 69, 2, 'Old and New Delhi\r\nNext day, soon after your hefty breakfast, we will set off to see Jama Masjid which also happens to the UNESCO World Heritage Site. Build by Emperor Akbar, it’s the architecture made out of Red Stone that stands tall. Next is a peep into the old lanes of Old Delhi. And here we shall take you across Birla Temple, Crematory of Mahatma Gandhi, Parliament House, and Red Fort. After lunch, it\'s Chandni Chowk and Kinari Bazar - the local cloth markets which you shall see around. Dinner and stay at the hotel.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(108, 69, 3, 'New Delhi - Mandawa\r\nThe next destination is Mandawa – by road. Mandawa which is basically is a small town in Rajasthan is famous for its Havelis, frescos on them and the fort – all of them hundreds of years old. We shall take you around the famous temples like Hanuman Prasad Goenka, Murmuria Jhunjhunwala and Gulab Rai Ladia Haveli. Soon after lunch we will see the Mandawa Fort built in 18th century. It is loaded with Lord Krishna paintings on the walls and ceilings; antiques and mirror work. Overnight stay will be at the hotel.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(109, 69, 4, 'Mandawa - Bikaner\r\nNext morning, soon after breakfast, we will set of towards Bikaner – one of most beautiful cities of Rajasthan. The tourist places we will see here include Junagarh Fort, Lalgarh Palace and Gajner Palace. After lunch here, we shall see Asia’s Largest Camel Breeding Research Farm. The evening is set for local market shopping and round about. Dinner and night stay at the hotel.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(110, 69, 5, 'Bikaner - Jaisalmer\r\nJaisalmer is a land of Rajasthani Temples, Fort. It’s at a distance of 330kms one has to cover to reach here from Bikaner. In the 5 hours drive we shall see the famous 7th Century Mahavira Jain Temple and 200 years old Jija Mata Temple. Lunch as enroute and we shall Jaisalmer in the evening. Check – in the hotel as you will be served refreshments. Night stay and dinner at the pre-booked hotel only.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(111, 69, 6, 'Exploring Jaisalmer\r\nThis land of Sun, encloses in itself some of the most beautiful places of Rajasthan. The best thing to see here is the Jaisalmer Fort. The beauty of the Fort is not only the ,, frescos, wall paintings and all – but also the 5000 people which it still houses! Yes, there are 5000 people still living the Fort – the blood generation of those who used to serve the generations of Maharajas of Jaisalmer! From the top of the fort, you can see the entire city, painted in Golden yellow. Next things to see here are the Patwon Ki Haveli and NathMal Ji Ki Haveli – a peek into how the old age temples used to be! Lunch is at one of the best restaurants of the city. In the evening we will drive you to Sand Dunes of Jaisalmer! Enjoy the sun setting here and move back to the hotel for dinner and night stay!', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(112, 69, 7, 'Jaisalmer - Jodhpur and Luni\r\nRustic life of Rajasthan - After enjoying our breakfast, we leave to Jodhpur. As we freshen up, in the afternoon, we visit the Mehrangarh Fort, which is 125 meters above the plains and constitutes beautiful place. As we get over with our sightseeing drive to Luni, we visit the palace amidst the more rustic life of Rajasthan. As we enjoy our lunch, we take you on a safari to discover the magnificent jungle beauty. You will be visiting the Bishnoi villages. We will be spending night in the Fort Chanwa in Luni and, our trip further.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(113, 69, 8, 'Luni - Ranakpur - Udaipur\r\nNext day after enjoying Jaisalmer we set off to Ranakpur via Luni. Ranakpur is famous for 15th century Jain Temples. After seeing these, we shall move on to Udaipur – the City of Lakes. Lunch is check-in and dinner and night stay at pre-booked hotel in Udaipur City.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(114, 69, 9, 'Exploring Udaipur\r\nUdaipur which is at an altitude of 577ML is surrounded by lakes. It is fun check place where you can see the City Palace which encloses the Worlds’ Largest Crystal Gallery by present Maharajah Gajner Singh Ji; Fateh Sagar Lakes with hundreds of catfish in it; Jagdish Temple and Sahelion ki Barii. In the evening we shall take to you see the dying art of India – the Puppet Show at Meera Kala Mandir. Dinner and night stay at the hotel itself.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(115, 69, 10, 'Udaipur - Jaipur\r\nUdaipur to Jaipur is a 6 hrs drive and we shall there in the afternoon. Soon after lunch we shall take to see the Jaipur Solar Observatory – Jantar Mantar and after this Hawa Mahal. Hawa Mahal built for the Queens to see the movements of the city from “Jharokahs” or small windows – is, an architectural marvel in itself! It’s it\'s storied semi–octagonal historical monument - not to be missed. Night stay and dinner at the hotel!', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(116, 69, 11, 'Exploring Jaipur\r\nThe day we will begin with seeing the Amer Fort. You can reach up either on the back of an elephant or by foot – the choice is yours! Next is the City Palace. Inside City Palace you can see the silver miniature museum, huge silver urns which Maharajah Sawai Singhji used to carry Ganges water on a trip to London, paintings and murals on the walls of the palace and the Devi Temple. A guided tour you will enjoy. The evening is set for a trip to Babu Market – the local Indian Cultural Market – you can shop here for Indian dresses and artifacts. Dinner at Chowki Dhani and night stay at the hotel.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(117, 69, 12, 'Jaipur - Fatehpur Sikri - Agra\r\nNext morning we shall set off to Fatehpur Sikiri – ages old city of Mughal Era. In the afternoon we will reach Agra. There after checking in Hotel, we shall move on to see one of the Seven Wonders of the World – the Taj Mahal. The monument which took 17 years to get completed and is epitome made of pure White Marble – is an epitome of love and a marvel to see! Night stay and dinner at hotel!', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(118, 69, 13, 'Exploring Agra\r\nSoon after breakfast after lunch, we shall set off to see Agra. Beginning from Agra Fort – the place from where Emperor Shah Jahan used to see the Taj Mahal. We will see other places like Tomb of Itimad-ud–Daulah, Chini Ka Rauza, Tomb of Great Akbar and Guru Ka Tal. Dinner and night stay in the hotel.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(119, 69, 14, 'Agra - Khajuraho\r\nIt’s a 7 hours drive from Agra to Khajuraho; so we will start early. We shall take you directly to the hotel in Khajuraho after which you can see the famous Khajuraho Temples. Located in Chatarpur District of Madhya Pradesh; it’s a UNESCO WORLD HERITAGE SITE and also considered one of the Seven Wonders of India. It’s the largest group of Medieval Hindu and Jain Temples – known for its erotic sculptures. Night stay with authentic Madhya Pradesh cuisine dinner at the hotel only!', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(120, 69, 15, 'Khajuraho - Varanasi\r\nNext morning we will catch a flight to Varanasi – the land of Ganges. Reaching here by noon, we will take you to Sarnath which is just 10kms away Sarnath is the place where Buddha preached for the first time after attaining enlightenment. After seeing this place, lunch shall be offered in the hotel. Evening you can spend taking a dip in the holy water of Ganges; seeing the world – famous Ganga Arti and taking a round of the Holy City. Night stay and dinner shall be at the hotel only.', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(121, 69, 16, 'Varanasi - Delhi\r\nNext morning, we shall take you for a boat ride in the serene waters of Ganges to see the Sunrise. In the afternoon, we shall take you to Varanasi Airport from where you shall be deported to New Delhi. In Delhi we will take you around Delhi markets – if you wish so; otherwise, we will escort you to the airport for your onward journey!', '2018-12-28 08:46:57', '2018-12-28 13:46:57'),
(122, 74, 1, 'edwstfre', '2018-07-27 05:40:49', '2018-07-27 05:40:49'),
(123, 75, 1, 'edwstfre', '2018-07-27 05:46:10', '2018-07-27 05:46:10'),
(124, 78, 1, 'Awaits warm welcomes on your arrival at New Delhi international airport/Railway station by the representative and transfer to the hotel. Check in to the hotel and after breakfast and fresh up, then proceed to the Sightseeing in Old Delhi Explore the Red Fort known as Lal Quila (A UNESCO World Heritage Site). The Red Fort was the residence of the Mughal emperor of India for nearly 200 years. It is Located in the center of Delhi and houses a number of museums. Next venture to the Jama Masjid the country\'s largest mosque, built in 1656, where thousands of Muslims offer prayers daily. The great mosque of Old Delhi is both the largest in India and the final architectural extravagance of Shah Jahan. The mosque\'s courtyard is capable of holding 25,000 devotees. Evening free for shopping. Then visit the New Delhi Sightseeing, Visit Humayun\'s Tomb (A UNESCO World Heritage Site), the tomb is an early example of Mughal architecture. This tomb is of great interest in relation to the Taj\r\nMahal. Tour Qutub Minar, (A UNESCO World Heritage Site), the Qutab Minar is a soaring tower of victory. It was construction was commenced in 1193, immediately after the defeat of the last Hindu Kingdom in Delhi.It\'s nearly 73 meters high and tapers from a 15-meter-diameter base to just 2.5 meters at the top. Go to India\'s Gate the national monument of India. Constructed in memory of 90,000 British-Indian soldiers who fought in WW-II. The structure was built under the leadership of Sir Edwin Lutyens. The architectural complex is made of red stone and granite. Drive past the official residence of the President of India and the Parliament House. The President\'s house is a famous attraction in New Delhi. It remained the home to the former British Viceroy of India till 1950. The Parliament House is a circular colonnaded building. It currently houses ministerial offices, numerous committee rooms, and an excellent library. Conceived in the Imperial Style, the Parliament\r\nHouse consists of an open verandah with 144 columns. Special Activities: Rickshaw ride in Old Delhi. Overnight stay in Delhi.', '2018-11-16 13:55:08', '2018-11-16 18:55:08'),
(125, 78, 2, 'New Delhi – Agra [210 Km/4 Hrs Approx.]\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast check out and drive to Agra (210 Km/4 Hrs approx.) upon arrival check into the hotel. Later visit Agra Fort – the seat and the stronghold of the Mughal Empire under successive generations. This was the seat of Mughal rule and administration and the present structure owes its origins to Akbar who erected the walls and gate and the first buildings on the eastern banks of Yamuna River. Shah Jehan added the impressive quarters and the mosque while Aurangzeb added the outer ramparts. Visit its Hall of Public Audience and its Royal Pavilions. Visit Taj Mahal with its spectacular views. The Taj Mahal, which is one man’s monumental testimony to love, has become synonymous not only with this city but with all of India. A mausoleum built by Shah Jahan for his empress Mumtaz Mahal, the Taj is the primary attraction of the city. The construction is believed to have taken 18 years (1631-1648) with over 20,000 artisans working around the clock. Overnight stay in the hotel.Special Activities: Golf cart ride at Taj Mahal in Agra', '2018-11-16 13:55:08', '2018-11-16 18:55:08'),
(126, 78, 3, 'Agra – Fatehpur Sikri - Jaipur [240 Km/5 Hrs]\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast check out and drive to Jaipur and stop at Fatehpur Sikri en route. Fatehpur Sikri was built by Emperor Akbar in 1569 and abandoned after 15 years due to the scarcity of water. See the graceful buildings including Jama Masjid, Tomb of Salim Chishti, Panch Mahal and other palaces. Later drive continuous to Jaipur, about 195 kilometers from Fatehpur Sikri. Then proceed to Jaipur. Upon arrival check in at the hotel. Head for a visit to the Jantar Mantar -an astronomical observatory, built by the founder King of Jaipur, with\r\nnineteen architectural astronomical instruments to observe the harmony of the heavens. The most significant one is the Samrat Yantra - popularly known as the world’s largest sundial. Drive past the Hawa Mahal or the “Palace of the Winds” - a five-story palace designed with\r\n953 windows adorned with intricate latticework. Overnight stay at the hotel in Jaipur.', '2018-11-16 13:55:08', '2018-11-16 18:55:08'),
(127, 78, 4, 'This day after breakfast, set out for Jaipur city tour. Proceed to visit the stunning fort of Jaipur - Amer Fort. It is a massive hill fort located on a hilltop dating back to the 16th century that displays private halls, pavilions, former private chambers of the Rajput Kings and royal\r\nwomen. Here, take an Elephant ride to and fro the fort absorbing the captivating reflections of this Fort falling on the Maota Lake below. Later in the afternoon, make a visit to the royal palace of Jaipur - City Palace that portrays a perfect fusion of Mughal and Rajput architecture. Here, explore the former private and public chambers, silver vessels, courtyards, gateways, private chambers of the King and lots more. It also houses a museum that showcases carpets, hand-written scriptures, manuscripts and various other artifacts that belonged to the royal family of Jaipur. Then drive to Ajmer. Jaipur - Ajmer (150 Km / 2-3 Hrs) Upon arrival check in at the hotel. Then visit the Adhai Din Ka Jhopra, Nasiyan Temple, and Ana Sagar Lake. Overnight stay at the hotel. Special Activities: Elephant ride at Amber fort Jaipur', '2018-11-16 13:55:08', '2018-11-16 18:55:08'),
(128, 78, 5, 'After breakfast visit, Ajmer Dargah Sharif then drives to the railway station for board train to Delhi. Train Ajmer - New Delhi (12016 @1545/2240 Hrs) After reaching Delhi, Departure Upon arrival departure transfer to the Airport to board flight /train for onward destination.', '2018-11-16 13:55:08', '2018-11-16 18:55:08'),
(129, 79, 1, 'Cochin – Munnar (130kms/4Hrs)\r\nOn arrival in Cochin Airport our cab will pick you up & transfer to the Munnar, on the way enjoy the beauty of waterfall ( Barrera waterfalls), tea gardens Later check in to the hotel, in evening visit local market overnight accommodation at the hotel.', '2018-11-20 04:40:48', '2018-11-20 09:40:48'),
(130, 79, 2, 'Munnar\r\nAfter breakfast proceeds for Rajamalai (Eravikulam) National Park – famous for Nilgiri Tahr (Wild goat), Anaimudi Peak – South India’s Highest Peak, Tata Tea Museum, Historical Church, Mattupetty, Echo Point, Kundala Lake, Photo Point International lossom (Hydel) Park, Headwork’s Dam, Spice Plantation. Overnight stay at the hotel in Munnar.', '2018-11-20 04:40:48', '2018-11-20 09:40:48'),
(131, 79, 3, 'Munnar – Alleppey (154kms/4.5Hrs)\r\nAfter Breakfast check out at the hotel. Transfer to Alleppey Houseboat/Hotel, Full day at disposal. Overnight stay at houseboat/Hotel in Alleppey.', '2018-11-20 04:40:48', '2018-11-20 09:40:48'),
(132, 79, 4, 'Alleppey - cochin (55km1.15Hrs)\r\nAfter breakfast check out from Houseboat/hotel.proceed to kochi.drop at Cochin airport/railway station.', '2018-11-20 04:40:48', '2018-11-20 09:40:48'),
(133, 80, 1, 'Cochin – Munnar (130kms/4Hrs)\r\n\r\nOn arrival in Cochin Airport/Railway station our cab will pick you up & proceed to Munnar, on the way enjoy the beauty of the waterfall, tea gardens Later check in to the hotel, in evening visit local market overnight accommodation at the hotel.', '2018-11-16 12:13:16', '2018-11-16 17:13:16'),
(134, 80, 2, 'Munnar\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast proceeds for Rajamalai (Eravikulam) National Park – famous for Nilgiri Tahr (Wild goat), Anaimudi Peak – South India’s Highest Peak, Tata Tea Museum, Historical Church, Mattupetty, Echo Point, Kundala Lake, Photo Point International blossom (Hydel) Park, Headwork’s Dam, Spice Plantation. Overnight stay at a hotel in Munnar', '2018-11-16 12:13:16', '2018-11-16 17:13:16'),
(135, 80, 3, 'Munnar – Thekkady (90kms/3Hrs)\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast proceed to Thekkady, the exotic Wildlife destination of Kerala. It’s also known as the spice bag of the state. You can enjoy a beautiful journey through the hills and valleys of Western Ghat to reach this jungle destination.also you can enjoy the misty route with a cool climate. Check in your hotel and later go for Spice plantation visit, elephant ride, or\r\nan Ayurvedic massage treatment there. Also, have an amazing boat ride in Periyar Lake (Direct Payment Basis) which flows through the Periyar tiger reserve. You will have a chance to watch the wild animals like elephant, Bison, Sambar, Deer etc. are roaming both shores, Rest of the day at disposal to explore the surroundings by owns. Overnight stay at the hotel in Thekkady.', '2018-11-16 12:13:16', '2018-11-16 17:13:16'),
(136, 80, 4, 'Thekkady – Alleppey (150kms/5Hrs)\r\n\r\nAfter Breakfast check out from the hotel. Proceed to Alleppey Arrive at Alleppey ready for the thrilling experience on the backwaters of Kerala. On this leisurely cruise, you will enjoy \r\nbeautiful villages, paddy fields, small churches, temples and witness the day-to-day life of the villagers. Overnight at the Hotel.', '2018-11-16 12:13:16', '2018-11-16 17:13:16'),
(137, 80, 5, 'Alleppey – Cochin ( 80 kms/2.5Hrs)\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast check out from the houseboat, Today you are transferred to Cochin airport for your onward journey to home.', '2018-11-16 12:13:16', '2018-11-16 17:13:16'),
(138, 81, 1, 'Chandigarh – Shimla (110 kms/4 hrs)\r\nChandigarh is the gateway to your journey. You\'ll be picked from Chandigarh Airport/railway station and transferred by our representatives to Shimla. It is snuggled in the Shivalik Ranges and is a stunning place to visit with exotic glimpses of the snow-capped Himalayan ranges and far stretching valleys. On entering this destination, you will check in at the hotel and rest for the night. Overnight in Shimla.', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(139, 81, 2, 'Day trip to Kufri; Naldehra & Mashobra\r\nEnjoy the breakfast at the hotel. After that, you will be taken on an outing to the skiing resort of Kufri. Kufri is also well known for its skiing activities and ski resorts. You may also Visit the Wildlife Sanctuary and the Fun World Amusement Park in Kufri. On your return, you may also visit Mashobra and Naldehra golf course. Here you can have some great time with your family and friends. In the afternoon you are taken to visit some of the best city attractions such as Christ Church, Scandal Point, & Jakhu Temple, Sankat Mochan. In the evening you will enjoy shopping at The Mall and The Ridge. Overnight in Shimla.', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(140, 81, 3, 'Transfer to Manali via Kullu(240 km/8 hrs)\r\n\r\nPost breakfast, check out from the hotel in Shimla and travel by surface transport to Manali. En route, you may visit Sundarnagar Lake, Pandoh Dam, Kullu Valley, Kullu Shawl Factory, Vaishno Devi Temple, & Angora Rabbit Farm on way to Manali. On arrival in Manali, you will check-in at the hotel & retire for the night after dinner. Overnight in Manali', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(141, 81, 4, 'Trip to Solang Valley up to Snow Line\r\n\r\nThis day after breakfast move towards Solang valley, Gulaba, Jogni falls till the snow point (Rohtang trip on direct payment basis). Solang Valley in Manali is located at a distance of 13 km in a side valley at the top of the Kullu valley is an imposing valley between Solang village and Beas Kund. Solang valley offers the view of glaciers and snow capped mountains and\r\npeaks. Solang Valley has fine ski slopes. The Mountaineering Institute of Manali has installed a ski lift for training purpose. Located here is a hut and guest house of the Mountaineering and Allied Sports Institute, Manali. Now a few hotels have also come up. The winter skiing festival is organized in Solang Valley. Skiing and Paragliding are two main activities which are organized here. Apart from this many other adventure sports are available like Zorbing, Horse riding & Snow Motor Bikes riding etc. Evening return to the hotel for an overnight stay.', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(142, 81, 5, 'In Manali – Naggar Excursion & Local Sightseeing\r\n\r\nToday morning after breakfast, visit Naggar Castle. Naggar was the former capital of Kullu. Today this ancient and beautiful Palace is a popular tourist spot. Prof. Late Nicholas Roerich, a reputed artist had chosen Naggar as his residence when he came to India in 1929. The house has now been converted into an art gallery which houses numbers of rare paintings and other specimens of art in Naggar. After lunch, enjoy Manali Local Sightseeing. You may start your tour with a visit to the famous Hadimba Temple. Thereafter, visit the Vashist village, which is popular for its hot water springs and several revered shrines. Another must-visit place at this destination is Van Vihar, Tibetian Monastery & Club House. In the evening, you can either explore its numerous places of interest or take a stroll on the popular Mall Road.Later, return to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay. Overnight in Manali.', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(143, 81, 6, 'Departure to Chandigarh ( 120 km; 4 hours)\r\n\r\nToday is the last day of the Himachal Tour. Have your breakfast and complete the check-out formalities. Start driving towards Chandigarh Airport/Railway Station, ending your trip with sweet memories.', '2019-03-02 05:42:53', '2019-03-02 10:42:53'),
(144, 82, 1, 'Cochin – Munnar (130kms/4Hrs)\r\nOn arrival in Cochin Airport/Railway station our cab will pick you up & proceed to Munnar, on the way enjoy the beauty of the waterfall, tea gardens Later check in to the hotel, in evening visit local market overnight accommodation at the hotel.', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(145, 82, 2, 'Munnar Local SightSeeing\r\nAfter breakfast proceeds for Rajamalai (Eravikulam) National Park – famous for Nilgiri Tahr (Wild goat), Anaimudi Peak – South India’s Highest Peak, Tata Tea Museum, Historical Church, Mattupetty, Echo Point, Kundala Lake, Photo Point International blossom (Hydel) Park, Headwork’s Dam, Spice Plantation. Overnight stay at the hotel in Munnar', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(146, 82, 3, 'Munnar – Thekkady (90kms/3Hrs)\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, proceed to Thekkady, the exotic Wildlife destination of Kerala. It’s also known as the spice bag of the state. You can enjoy a beautiful journey through the hills and valleys of Western Ghat to reach this jungle destination.also you can enjoy the misty route with a cool climate. Check in your hotel and later go for Spice plantation visit, elephant ride, or an Ayurvedic massage treatment there. Also, have an amazing boat ride in Periyar Lake (Direct Payment Basis) which flows through the Periyar tiger reserve. You will have a chance to watch the wild animals like elephant, Bison, Sambar, Deer etc. are roaming both shores, \r\nRest of the day at disposal to explore the surroundings by owns. Overnight stay at the hotel in Thekkady.', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(147, 82, 4, 'Thekkady – Kumarakom (120km 3.30 hours)\r\n\r\nThe morning after breakfast, check out from the hotel and proceed to Kumarakom (A charming village). Arrive Kumarakom and check into the Homestay and enjoy the Kerala culture and lifestyle. Overnight stay at Hotel.', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(148, 82, 5, 'Kumarakom– Alleppey (45km- 1 hour)\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, check out from the hotel & Depart for Allepey (Famous for Backwaters). On arrival In Alleppey, check into the houseboat & enjoy Houseboat facilities  and sightseeing', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(149, 82, 6, 'Alleppey-Kovalam (160km)\r\n\r\nThe morning after breakfast, check out from the hotel Proceed to Kovalam at 10 am. (capture the essence of Kerala through en route of coastal ).. On arrival check in at Hotel at 1:30 pm. And rest of the day free for your leisure activities. Overnight Stay', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(150, 82, 7, 'Kovalam – Trivandrum Local\r\n\r\nMorning at 11 am depart to enjoy full day sightseeing city tour of Trivandrum – Visit Museum & Zoo, Padmanabha Swami Temple, Sri Chitra Art Gallery, Nappier Museum and Veli Village. Evening visits the spectacular Kovalam. Overnight stay at Kovalam.', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(151, 82, 8, 'Kovalam - Cochin Drop.( 216 km-6 hours )\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast check out from the hotel at 8:00 am and proceed to Cochin airport/railway station to connect flight/train for your onward journey with sweet and fond memories. (Or you can take flight or train from Trivandrum itself)', '2018-11-15 12:52:43', '2018-11-15 17:52:43'),
(152, 83, 1, 'On your arrival at Calicut Airport/ Railway station meet our representative and drive to Wayanad(80 Kms) the extraordinary destination of Kerala with a bundle of attractions as well as it’s an experience in the lap of Nature for every traveler. Check in your hotel, have leisure and overnight stay near Edakal caves', '2019-11-30 11:44:35', '2019-11-30 16:44:35'),
(153, 83, 2, 'After breakfast proceeds to the wild Wayanad as you can visit Edakkal cave which is situated on the top of Ambukkuthimala with a view of three states as well as the spot has many carvings of the stone age and one should truck and climb the hill to reach the cave. After lunch visit Soojippara Waterfall one of the major spots in Wayanad as a typical natural fall where you can take bath and enjoy a lot. Overnight stay.', '2019-11-30 11:44:35', '2019-11-30 16:44:35'),
(154, 83, 3, 'Today your sightseeing will be at Kuruwa island as it’s known as the largest island created by the river Kabani with a fabulous view of Forest and evergreen vegetation. Afternoon you can visit the Tholpetty wildlife sanctuary, with Exiting jeep and other recreational activities. Later, back to your resort and overnight stay.', '2019-11-30 11:44:35', '2019-11-30 16:44:35'),
(155, 83, 4, 'Check out your resort after breakfast, Proceed to Banasura as it’s known as the largest earth Dam in India with a fabulous view of river bansura and evergreen vegetation. Afternoon you can visit Pookot Lake, one of the best-maintained picnic spots in Wayanad with ample\r\nfacilities for boating and other recreational activities. After that drive towards Calicut(75 kms/2hrs) Airport/Railway stations for the onward journey.', '2019-11-30 11:44:35', '2019-11-30 16:44:35'),
