(2, 'Kerala', 'Thrissur', 'image/destinations/thrichivaperoor.jpg', 'February', 'April', 2, 6, 'Cochin International Airport', 'Thrissur Railway Station', '', '', '<h1><strong>1) Athirappilly Waterfalls</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.nativeplanet.com/img/2016/09/athi7-23-1474635902.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Athirappilly Falls</em>, is situated in Athirappilly Panchayat, Chalakudy Taluk, Thrissur District of Kerala, India on the Chalakudy River, which originates from the upper reaches of the Western Ghats at the entrance to the Sholayar ranges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>2) Thrissur Zoo</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/kaayalmedia/2017/07/24/Chimmony-wildlife-sanctuary-2.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Thrissur Zoo</em>&nbsp;or State Museum &amp; Zoo, Thrissur (formerly the&nbsp;<em>Trichur Zoo</em>) is a 13.5-acre (5.5 ha) zoo that opened in 1885 in the heart of Thrissur City, Kerala, India. It is one of the oldest zoos in the country, and is home to the wide variety of animals, reptiles, and birds</p>', '<h1><strong>1) Garuda Hotel</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.hotelroomsearch.net/im/hotels/asia/id/garuda-hotel-4.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to The&nbsp;<em>Garuda Hotel</em>, where luxury meets contemporary offering everyone around the globe the concept of home away from home. Located in the heart of Thrissur town, this crest of comfort is extremely proximate to the railway station and the bus stand making it easily accessible.</p>', NULL, '<h1><strong>1) Dolours Basilica</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://tourstokerala.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Basilica-of-our-Lady-of-Dolores-Church1.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Lady of&nbsp;<em>Dolours Basilica</em>&nbsp;alias Puthanpally is a minor basilica of the Syro-Malabar Catholic Church in Thrissur City in the Indian state of Kerala. The third tallest church in Asia, it is famous for its Gothic style architecture.</p>', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> :&nbsp;There are regular buses from other major cities of the country to Thrissur.Bus Station(s):&nbsp;<strong>Trichur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air :&nbsp;</strong>Thrissur does not have an airport. Nearest airport is Kochi Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> :&nbsp;You can easily get regular trains to Thrissur from other major cities of the country.Railway Station(s):&nbsp;<strong>Thrissur (TCR),&nbsp;</strong><strong>Divine Nagar (DINR),&nbsp;</strong><strong>Thrissur Punkunnam (PNQ)</strong></p>\r\n', '<h1><strong>1) Sobha City Mall</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.businesszoom.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Sobha_City_Mall6.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sobha City Mall is a shopping mall in Sobha City, Puzhakkal, Thrissur City, Kerala, India.The Mall opened on December 17, 2015. It is built on 4.7 acres land and a super built up area of more than 600,000 square feet</p>', NULL, '<p><strong>Winter Season in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Winter begins in Thrissur in December and remains till the mid of February. The minimum and maximum temperature of this magnificent city remains in between 22&deg;C to 30&deg; C respectively. The climate remains quite enjoyable and it is an ideal time for tourists to go for outdoor activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Summer Season in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The summer season in the cultural city begins in the month of March and ends in the month of May. During summer, city&rsquo;s minimum temperature remains on the warmer side and the maximum temperature remains round 38&deg; C. It is a perfect time for indoor activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Best Season in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thrissur mainly has tropical climate therefore one will find the city on the hot and humid side. The best time to visit Thrissur is the season of winter when tourists will find the climate on the pleasant and enjoyable side. During this season, you can take pleasure in the outdoor visits as well as sightseeing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Monsoon Season in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The city experiences the monsoon season from June and remains till September. Heavy rainfall occurs during this season especially in the months of July. To feel the pleasure and bliss of rain, number of travelers of different parts of the country as well as world love to pay a visit here with their dear and near ones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are numbers of hotels in Thrissur which offer great comfort as well as facilities to their customers. Most of the renowned hotels are mainly located in the center of the city. Moving in the city, you will find various types of hotels such as luxury hotels, budget hotels and lodges. The best thing which you will like about these Thrissur hotels is their hospitality. Each and every staff strives to offer world class services to its customers so that they can carry unforgettable memories with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://blog.travelwithsmile.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/ThrissurPooram-Kuda-Copy.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Events / Festivals in Thrissur</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Being a land of Pooram, Thrissur is one of the top pooram amongst all the poorams. The city celebrates some of the famous festivals such as Arattupuzha Pooram, Machadu Mamangam and Kodungallur Bharani. Thrissur Pooram is the most impressive and vivid festival of the state of Kerala. It is celebrated at Vadakkumnathan temple in the month of April. The festival was introduced by the Maharaja of the erstwhile Cochin State in the late 18th century. Arattupuzha Pooram is another festival which is celebrated after the Thrissur Pooram. Here, eight days festival known as Kodungallur Bharani is celebrated in the months of March-April (Meenam).</p>', NULL, 'thichivaperoor', '2018-06-23 11:11:06', '2018-04-23 22:51:46'),
(3, 'Karnataka', 'Bengluru', 'image/destinations/bangluru936006203.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 3, 6, 'Kempegowda International Airport', 'Krantivira Sangolli Rayanna (Bengaluru)', 'Bengaluru (also called Bangalore) is the capital of India\'s southern Karnataka state. The center of India\'s high-tech industry, the city is also known for its parks and nightlife. By Cubbon Park, Vidhana Soudha is a Neo-Dravidian legislative building. Former royal residences include 19th-century Bangalore Palace, modeled after England’s Windsor Castle', NULL, '<h2><strong>1) Lal Bagh</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/ehimages/2017/10/11/img_bb89f3a8af27ac7b35206435122ecb02_1507720310114_original.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lalbagh or Lalbagh Botanical Gardens, meaning The Red Garden in English, is a well-known botanical garden in southern Bengaluru, India. It has a famous glass house dating from 1889 which hosts two annual flower shows (26 January and 15 August). Lalbagh houses India&#39;s largest collection of tropical plants</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2) Cubbon Park</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/images.deccanchronicle.com/dc-Cover-1dmhvguf0v9q09e1npuru9fsi6-20170518034039.Medi.jpeg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Cubbon Park</em>, Officially called Sri Chamarajendra Park is a landmark &#39;lung&#39; area of the Bengaluru city, located within the heart of the city in the Central Administrative Area. Originally created in 1870, when Major General Richard Sankey was the then British Chief Engineer of Mysore state</p>', '<h2><strong>1) CourtYard Bengluru Hebbal</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/12/75/5b/88/the-hebbal-cafe.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Amidst the lush greenery and bustling business hub of the Garden city, Courtyard by&nbsp;<em>Marriott Bengaluru Hebbal</em>&nbsp;makes your stay a fun and delightful affair. The thoughtful amenities clubbed with our enticing services will leave you feeling re-energized. Courtyard fosters warm and inviting spaces in our cleverly designed</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2)&nbsp;The Chancery Pavilion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<em>Chancery Pavilion</em>, is located in Ashok Nagar near MG Road, Residency Road, Richmond Town and Chickpet Bangalore. Book online and get the best deals on official website</p>', '<h2><strong>1)&nbsp;Our Native Village - Eco Resort near Bangalore</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/simplotel/image/upload/x_0,y_78,w_1500,h_844,r_0,c_crop,q_60,fl_progressive/w_960,f_auto,c_fit/our-native-village/Our_Native_Village_Garden_qg7zvy\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong><br />\r\nAll reviewsbullock cart ridekite flyinggilli danda<em>village</em>&nbsp;games<em>eco resortvillage</em>&nbsp;experiencepottery makingmud roadcow milkingpet friendly place<em>village</em>&nbsp;stylepet loverspets are allowedbon fire<em>resort</em>stafflong weekendapproach road</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2)&nbsp;Olde Bangalore Resort and Convention Centre</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://r1imghtlak.mmtcdn.com/ab33edbc6b8111e78b490a4cef95d023.jpg?interpolation=progressive-bicubic&amp;downsize=700:360&amp;output-quality=50\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Located within a close proximity to the Bangalore International Airport; around 12 km,&nbsp;<em>Olde Bangalore</em>is amongst the serene and appealing&nbsp;<em>resort</em>&nbsp;hotels around Bangalore. With a tradition ... 7; If cancellations are made within 0-<em>2</em>&nbsp;days before the start date of the trip, 50% of total tour cost will be charged as cancellation fees</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<h2><strong>1) Iskon Temple Banglore</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bangaloretourism.org/image/iskcon_temple_bangalore.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sri Radha Krishna&nbsp;<em>Temple</em>&nbsp;has deities of Radha and Krishna located at Rajajinagar, in North<em>Bangalore</em>, Karnataka, India. It is one of the largest&nbsp;<em>ISKCON temples</em>&nbsp;in the world. The&nbsp;<em>temple</em>&nbsp;is a huge cultural complex that was inaugurated in 1997 by Shankar Dayal Sharma</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2) Phoenix Marketcity</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Phoenix Market City</em>&nbsp;(Chennai) is a shopping mall developed by Phoenix Mills Limited located in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India. It was opened in January 2013 and is the largest mall in the city. Contents. [hide]. 1 About; 2 Entertainment; 3 See also; 4 References. About[edit].&nbsp;<em>Phoenix Market City</em>,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>By road :&nbsp;</strong>Bangalore is well-connected by a network of buses from cities like Goa, Mumbai, Pune, Coimbatore and Mangalore. The options range from regular buses to air-conditioned, Volvo and sleeper coaches. While some of the buses are run by Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation, there are also a number of private bus operators who run inter-city buses to and from Bangalore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail :&nbsp;</strong>Bangalore has two important railway stations - Bengaluru City Railway Station and Yeswantpur Junction. Both railway stations have regular trains running from Delhi, Mumbai, Pune and other major cities. For travelling within Bangalore, there is Namma Metro (with limited connectivity), which is an intra-city rail network set up by the Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air :&nbsp;</strong>Bangalore is extremely well-connected by regular flights from Delhi, Mumbai and most other important cities in India and also has international carriers flowing in and out of the Bengaluru International Airport, which is located about 40 kilometres from the main city. A taxi from the airport would take about 45 minutes to reach the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<h2><strong><em>1)&nbsp;</em>Brigade Road&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://photos.wikimapia.org/p/ot2/00/00/04/51/47_big.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Brigade Road</em>&nbsp;is one of the biggest commercial centres and busiest shopping areas of Bangalore, the state capital of Karnataka, India. It is also a connecting road between the&nbsp;<em>M G Road</em>&nbsp;and Residency Road in the city</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2)&nbsp;Commercial Street Bangalore&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://imgstaticcontent.lbb.in/lbbnew/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/12/shivajinagar.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, we know&nbsp;<em>Commercial Street</em>&nbsp;is a haven for shopaholics. From the simplest of trinkets to the trendiest of clothes, we bet you will find them all at this place. But, it&#39;s not always easy to navigate this maze of stores to find what you want. We went exploring the area, just to pick out the best spots for you to head to</p>', '<h2><strong>1)&nbsp;Meat &amp; Eat</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://content3.jdmagicbox.com/comp/bangalore/s9/080pxx80.xx80.170928192035.w1s9/catalogue/meat-and-eat-dommasandra-bangalore-restaurants-ne6zj.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Meat</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Eat</em>&nbsp;is the brand of KAVI Group, ME is chain of restaurants where tasty fried chicken, burgers, kebabs, biryanis etc. are served hot and fresh under great ambiance. Product images are for illustration purpose only. Actual product may vary. This website is conceptual, not a legal offering</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>2) Mahesh Lunch Home</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://static.foodrhythms.net/images/restaurants/original/juhu_big1.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Mahesh Lunch Home</em>&nbsp;is a Seafood specialty restaurant which has now become one of the most popular and best Seafood restaurants chain in India. Drop in at our best seafood restaurants, now available at your nearest places like Juhu, Andheri, Navi Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore and Dubai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>3) Edo Japanese&nbsp;Restaurant and Bar</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://im1.dineout.co.in/images/uploads/restaurant/sharpen/4/b/w/p4812-143860578655bf61dacf606.jpg?w=1200\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" />&nbsp;<br />\r\nITC Gardenia, Richmond Road; Get&nbsp;<em>Menu</em>, Reviews, Contact, Location, Phone Number, Maps and more for&nbsp;<em>Edo Restaurant</em>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<em>Bar</em>&nbsp;- ITC Gardenia&nbsp;<em>Restaurant</em>&nbsp;on Zomato.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-c665b1d3dccaa9b35627adba22c3919e-c\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangalore enjoys moderate climate throughout the year and one can visit this magnificent city at any time of the year with utmost ease. However, the months between September and February see the highest tourist inflow to the city because the weather becomes even more pleasant during the winter season. Here&#39;s a seasonal break-up so you can plan your trip better:&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>October to February:</strong>&nbsp;The winter months in Bangalore are the best time to visit the city. It doesn&#39;t really get very cold with the lowest temperature dipping to about 10&deg;C. With so many lakes and gardens to visit, sightseeing and outdoor activities are most comfortable at this time. You wouldn&#39;t need heavy woolens but carry a light jacket, especially for the nights, which tend to get chilly. This is also a good time to plan getaways from Bangalore since there are a number of tourist attractions just outside Bangalore.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>March to May:&nbsp;</strong>While winters are over, the temperature is still pleasant. The maximum temperature doesn&#39;t usually cross 36&deg;C even in the hottest months making it perfect for the summers as well.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>June to September:</strong>&nbsp;Monsoons begin by the end of May and come with mild to heavy rainfall. August and September can see heavy showers but they are rarely continuous so you can still plan a trip without the rain becoming a dampener. Just carry an umbrella and a sturdy pair of shoes, and you are good to go.</p>', NULL, 'bengluru', '2018-10-04 11:21:59', '2018-10-04 15:21:59'),
(5, 'Kerala', 'Kochi', 'image/destinations/kochi893479687.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 2, 4, 'Cochin International Airport (25 km)', 'Ernakulam Junction (7 km)', NULL, '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Kochi or Cochin Known as the queen of the Arabian Sea, is the financial capital of Kerala and highly growing as a metro city , Kochi is a major seaport which held within the Ernakulum district of Kerala., Kochi has known as a key place in the spice trading business from as early as the 14th century AD.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Kochi has seen much cultural diversity. Today all of her histories results in an eclectic confluence of cultures; from&nbsp; Portuguese residences to the crumbling remains of the British Raj from 600-year-old fishing nets, to centuries-old synagogue. You can<br />\r\nfind a big versatility in a small space, and also enjoy the rush of a big township.</p>', '<h2><strong>Take the Ferry</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.theirishworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ulysses-500x324.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take the ferry to Ernakulam or Vypin and feel the endless swirl of the water. And also you can enjoy them</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Kochi-Muziris Biennale</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hindustantimes.com/rf/image_size_960x540/HT/p2/2016/12/16/Pictures/_47c19daa-c38f-11e6-913d-826c0833a15d.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have you ever seen a city turn into a live art exhibition? Kochi will show you. Starting in December, the Kochi-Muziris Biennale<br />\r\nlasts till March. Artists from all over the world come here to display their work and the city space becomes the site of exhibition. Paintings, sculptures, videos, photographs, graffiti, music and all kinds of performances bring the city to life. This, no doubt, is a must do at Kochi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Indo-Portuguese Museum</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/5b/47/ba/5b47bac329a614c0a1e590a23ce1c295.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kochi was one of India&rsquo;s first European colonies, This fort which Occupied by the Portuguese from 1503 to 1530, Before the Portuguese eventually discovered Goa and proceed further north up the shore, they built Fort Emmanuel (this is where the place gets the Fort Kochi nomenclature). Today, very little of the Fort is still protected.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Explore Vypin</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://c1.staticflickr.com/7/6071/6066765882_9440732300_b.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vypin is today one of the most populated islands in all of Asia. Enjoy this 27 kilometers long Island that was created in 1341, after effect of a massive flood. Enjoy the wade on the Cherai Beach, sunsets at Nadungad, and enjoy the 16th Century Pallipuram Fort. There&rsquo;s a lot on offer and Vypin hits high on the wonder of the big things to do in Kochi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Kerala Kathakali Centre</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/trell/f_auto,fl_progressive,t_medium/user-content/images/orig/qJUwyyxKXzfKLyeIz6Sw.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the prominent place to watch a Kathakali performance in Kerala. The channels likes of National Geographic BBC and Lonely Planet have featured their shows. They host three performances each evening and remain open all around the year (including weekends). Catch the hour-long Kalaripayattu performance starting at 4 p.m.; watch the complicated make- up of Kathakali artists (this takes 1 hour). After that, they will immerse yourself in the one and half hour long recital.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Take a Walk By the Beach</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.phnompenhpost.com/sites/default/files/styles/full-screen_watermarked/public/field/image/khmer-beach_0.jpg?itok=iBHzbFvS\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>International Pepper Exchange</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/02/c9/18/a9/mattancherry.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>it is the world&rsquo;s only pepper exchange. Headquartered in Kochi, the International Pepper Exchange is an internationally recognized, one of its kind organization which trades in varieties of pepper. started in 1997</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/images.deccanchronicle.com/dc-Cover-anfegbfra3ee1mvanbf11fr9a2-20170916005443.Medi.jpeg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong>: Cochin International Airport is a major one, situated in Nedumbassery near to Kochi and it has regular flights to a number of cities in the Middle East and South East Asia besides being fairly well connected to the rest of India. Numerous domestic carriers have daily flights to Kochi from across the country. The airport is known for its unique Keralan architecture and it&#39;s showing a miniature of art and culture of the land, the airport has separate terminals for domestic and international flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train:</strong> The two stations in the city are the Ernakulam Junction and Ernakulam Town. The station has a large food court, a medical store, a bookstore and clean waiting areas. Most long-distance trains passing through Ernakulam Junction. The metro train service also you can enjoy the heart of the city</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road:</strong> Kochi is well connected by roadways to major cities in south India. The Kerala State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC)&nbsp; operates several inter and intrastate buses to major cities around Cochin. The private buses also operate in the nearby sightseeing points of Kochi. The buses ply daily and are available in no-frills, standard and premium categories to suit all types of travelers. Some of the major highways leading to Kochi are the NH66, NH49 and the NH544. Kochi can act as the main hub of other destinations in Kerala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Water:</strong> cruises and boats are part of the mode of transportation of Kochi. One can opt to get into Kochi by ship as well. Yachts and cruise ships ply from Lakshadweep, Mumbai, Goa, Colombo, and Male. Leading premium international cruises to US and Europe also operate from Kochi.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://letsgokerala.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Jews.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will get en number of antique items and handicrafts items from the Jewish street Mattancheri. And you can purchase all the branded things from the biggest lulu mall of Asia which situated in Edapalli.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wetu.com/Resources/39613/the_malabar_house_kochi_1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kochi is a food hub. It serves hoards of foreign and Indian tourists on a regular basis. And like all tourist destinations, Kochi to is scattered with a different of cafes and eateries. The shacks on the way to the beach and even on the seashore will catch you with their exquisite seafood menu. Be sure to not miss, Ginger House, Oy&rsquo;s Restaurant, kayees biriyani hut, Malabar Junction and Kashi Art Caf&eacute; on your visit</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tripcrafters.com/images/articles/slides/3971-1492762895.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The best time to visit would be from September to February when the weather is delightful and enjoyable. The city does not feel a comprehensive change in temperatures during the year because of its typically tropical weather condition. However, it does have a distinct wet monsoon season. With heavy rains from May to July, most travelers try and avoid a trip during this time. Summers also right to travel because there is a chance for small rain on that time, so the weather will be a moderate, but sometimes it may hike to 40&deg; C that not that much pleasing for a traveler.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<h2><strong>Santacruz Basilica</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://images.freeimages.com/images/premium/previews/2219/22196015-santa-cruz-cathedral-basilica.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Santacruz Basilica was built in 1502 by the Portuguese, This is Asia&rsquo;s first cathedral and first European church in India. It was announced as a Basilica by Pope John Paul II. home is filled with several artifacts and historical paintings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Paradesi Synagogue</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://previews.agefotostock.com/previewimage/medibigoff/f16a68db20533da93368cd277bc4168a/ibr-4120085.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Created in 1568 after allowing Jewish refugees a home in Kerala during the time of Crusades, the Paradesi Synagogue still protected and remains as one of the very few functional ones in India. the Synagogue is the oldest one in the commonwealth. Located on Jew Street, the area was shelter to many Jews till the formation of Israel. The street is a heritage zone with many handicraft and antique shops.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Cheenavalas</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-5kA3YkGTn-w/Uq2zDwtdQ2I/AAAAAAAALYc/xZvNFcvyebQ/s1600/kochi-fishingnet-vaish.JPG\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cheenavalas are Chinese fishing nets which were originally gifted by Chinese King Kubalagi in the 14thcentury to the Maharaja of Travancore. These have now formed as an iconic symbol of Kochi. It helps make for an extraordinary capture against the frame of the reddish skies at time of sunset.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Cultural Hub</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://inhabitat.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/1/files/2013/07/SAMOO-Buk-Seoul-Museum-of-Art.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kochi is also an important center for the arts of Kerala and you must not miss an opportunity to see a&nbsp;performance of Kathakali and Kalaripayattu when here. Lots of&nbsp;temples and museums are in Kochi, along with its pristine&nbsp;perfect beaches offer an ecstasy feeling to each traveler.</p>', 'kochi', '2018-10-04 11:15:37', '2018-10-04 15:15:37'),
(7, 'Kerala', 'Munnar', 'image/destinations/munnar217564409.jpeg', 'September', 'February', 3, 8, 'Cochin International Airport', 'Aluva Railway Station', 'Munnar is a town in the Western Ghats mountain range in India’s Kerala state. A hill station and former resort for the British Raj elite, it\'s surrounded by rolling hills dotted with tea plantations established in the late 19th century. Eravikulam National Park, a habitat for the endangered mountain goat Nilgiri tahr, is home to the Lakkam Waterfalls, hiking trails and 2,695m-tall Anamudi Peak.', NULL, '<h3>Enjoy the flora &amp; fauna</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.keralaleisureholidays.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/nilgiri-tahr-single.jpg\" style=\"height:525px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can enjoy the vegetation of the sanctuary falls under six categories (according to Champion and Seth, 1968, and Chandrasekaran, 1962). They are Southern tropical thorn forest (Scrub jungle), Southern dry mixed deciduous forest (Dry deciduous forest), Southern moist mixed deciduous forest (Moist deciduous forest), Tropical riparian fringing forest (Riparian forest), Southern montane wet temperate forest (Hill shola forest) and Southern montane wet grassland (Grasslands). The predominant vegetation is a dry deciduous forest followed by scrub forest. Together they constitute about half of the total area which is in the low altitude areas. The riparian fringing forests are found on the hill folds and shola forests constitute a small portion.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Enjoy the misty climate</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://img.manoramaonline.com/content/dam/mm/en/travel/travel-news/images/2020/1/4/munnar-snow1.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cool climate is the best suit for honeymooners and families. In a day, the climate is moderate and allows you to get pleasure from all the trinkets of the beautiful hill station. The weather here generally rise and fall from 23 degree Celsius to 30 degree Celsius in December. Munnar is a destination in Kerala is appropriate to celebrate Christmas vacations with family or friends.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Take a cozy resort and enjoy the stay</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.ekeralatourism.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Niraamaya-Retreats-Cardamom-Club.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Being among one of the best Munnar resorts, it is located at a scenic location, covered with a green blanket of nature. It offers an outdoor pool, restaurant and free parking facilities to their guests. You can enjoy a series of activities inside the resort. They have special staff who look after the entertainment activities for the guests.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://img.manoramaonline.com/content/dam/mm/en/travel/celebrity-travel/images/2019/4/22/sayanora-travel8.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" />Munnar is one f the tourist spot in Kerala, the city is well connected by roads, rail, and air. The closest airport is located 105 km away at Cochin, while the railway station is just 105 km, State-run, as well as private buses, connect Munnar to major cities and towns in Kerala and neighboring states. State highways connect Munnar to other places. A drive down these roads is quite picturesque and memorable.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>By&nbsp;Air</strong>:&nbsp;The closest airport to Alleppey is the Cochin International Airport located &nbsp;105 km away.&nbsp;All major domestic carriers fly to Cochin. Some international carriers that connect to Cochin are Singapore Airlines, Jet Airways, Qatar Airways, Gulf Air and Etihad Airways.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>By Rail</strong>: The Aluva Railway Station is 103km from the city center. Major metropolitan cities like Delhi, Bengaluru, Chennai, Hyderabad, Mumbai, and Kolkata&nbsp;are connected to Aluva by the Indian railways. You could take a taxi, bus to reach in the Munnar city.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>By&nbsp;Road</strong>:&nbsp;Munnar has the best and well-maintained roadsMunnar is well connected by State Highways. The best merit is the natural beauty that runs along with the best roadways. There are a lot of bus services from different district of Kerala, there is a good network of state government buses and private buses.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://seoimgak.mmtcdn.com/blog/sites/default/files/images/Spices.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" />Munnar is having splendid shops, Find homemade chocolates, marshmallows, and cheese in the bakeries &ndash; awesome all the way! You will get plenty of flavored &nbsp;Tea powder in the nook and corner of the town. The street-side small stores will amaze you with an immense array of flowers, vegetables, handmade articles, hot snacks, children&#39;s toys, medicinal herbs, oils, and almost every useful thing.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.munnar.holiday/munnartourism/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/popular-vegetarian-food-in-munnar-kerala-800x385.jpg\" style=\"height:385px; width:800px\" />If you are a foodie, the lip-smacking charm of South Indian dishes like dosas and idlis is no secret to inland tourists. However, what most people don&rsquo;t know is that Munnar has a thriving street food culture that stirs to life when the sun goes down. From Puttu and kadala curry to appams with stew, the sheer diversity of Munnar food will make it hard for you to choose the menu. Also, you can taste<strong> </strong>Kerala Prawn Curry, &nbsp;Spicy Chicken Fry, Kerala Style Beef Fry, All the restaurants are experts to serve all the things.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://qphs.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-8d6eca9503060f4d90c657ccfe1b8d4f\" style=\"height:190px; width:602px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best time to visit Munnar is from August to February, So, this is the finest climate to visit Munar. Generally, Temperatures will be in the region of a comfortable 25&deg;C to a bracing 10&deg;C. If you are pointing the Eravikulam National park, sometimes the park will close due to the breeding period of Neelagiri Thar, commonly it&#39;s coming on the time of march end.</p>', '<h3><strong>Eravikulam National Park</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.keralatourism.org/images/eco-tourism/trekking_thumb/trekking-trails/eravikulam_28072018105517.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most sought after destination in Munnar is the&nbsp;Eravikulam National Park, the first of its kind in Kerala, where the endangered Nilgiri Thar. is protected. Spread over 97 sq. km., this park holds the largest viable population of Tahr, several other species of rare animals, birds, and butterflies. The park offers a magnificent view.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Explore Maryoor</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://lookerala.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/marayur-752x440.jpg\" style=\"height:440px; width:752px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Marayoor has excellent geographical topography that is best suitable for conducting activities like trekking. Thus, with unmatched pristine natural beauty, Marayoor has won a place among the must-see places when planning for a holiday at Munnar. Marayoor is a prominent destination that lying on the eastern side of the Western Ghats at about 40 km from Munnar is Marayoor, one of the most sought-after hill stations. Rich in scenic beauty and a number of attractions, this little hill station is less explored when compared with Munnar. One of the major fact for which Marayoor is famous for is the Sandalwood forests. Marayoor is the only place in Kerala that houses the natural sandalwood forests. These forests are maintained and conserved by the Kerala Forest Department and a refreshing stroll through these forests requires permission from the Forest department. forests, Kanthalloor, Dolmens, Marayoor jaggery, etc. Another major attraction at Marayoor is the Dolmens (or the Muniyara) which are believed to be stone coffins having underground tunnels. These Dolmens are built-up using rocks and they date back to the Neolithic period. Many of these Dolmens made from stone can be found near the old Siva Temple at Kovilkadavu and near the river Pambar. Out of the several Dolmens (or Muniyara) discovered some had fragments of burial urn near them; indicating that these were used as burial chambers. While the others having greater height are believed to have been used for the habitation of people.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Chinnar wildlife sanctuary</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.keralatourism.org/images/destination/large/chinnar_wildlife_sanctuary_in_idukki20131031103529_218_1.jpg\" style=\"height:405px; width:720px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An ideal place for trekking, Chinnar is located in the rainshadow region of Western Ghats and receives very less amount of rainfall every year. Due to this extensive variation of rainfall, Chinnar is blessed with a wide array of habitat types like deciduous forests, dry thorn scrub, riparian forest, shoals, and grasslands. There is an extensive sandalwood forest nearby the sanctuary, which is an added attraction. The 90km sq sanctuary is unique with its floral, ecological, geomorphology, and cultural significance. Chinnar is a unique thorny scrub forest with xerophyte species. This sanctuary is one of the 12 protected areas of Kerala.Chinnar has about 1000 species of flowering plants and a wide variety of medicinal plants. You can sight here 225 recorded species of birds and also the endangered species of Giant Grizzled Squirrel of India. Other important mammals that you can see here are elephant, tiger, leopard, gaur, sambar, spotted deer, Nilgiri Tahr, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Enjoy the mist in the top station </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tourmyindia.com/states/kerala/images/Top-Station-Munnar-1.jpg\" style=\"height:341px; width:467px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ou will get a beautiful hilltop view from the top of the hill. The highest point (1700m) on the Munnar-Kodaikanal road, Top Station offers a panoramic view of the majestic Western Ghats. The rare Neelakurinji (Strobilanthus), for which the destination is popular, blooms once in twelve years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Neelakurinji Munnar</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.keralatourism.org/images/picture/large/Blooming_of_Neelakurinji_1851.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is on o the enchanting and panoramic view on the Munnar hilltop. The biological phenomenon of the mass blooming of the Neelakurinji (Strobilanthus) flower that takes place once in twelve years has once again arrived in the famed hill resort of Munnar. Neela means blue in Malayalam language and Kurinji the local name of the flower.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Echo Point Munnar</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://keralatourism.travel/images/places-to-visit/headers/echo-point-munna-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg\" style=\"height:448px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This scenic place gets its name from the natural echo phenomenon here. Echo Point, situated on the way to Top Station from Munnar</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Meesapulimala</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://munnar.kfdcecotourism.com/images/acti-meeshapulimala.jpg\" style=\"height:420px; width:770px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Near to the famous hill station, Munnar in Kerala is a lesser-known destination called Meesappulimala &ndash; a destination for the highly adventurous. The second highest peak in the Western Ghats, where you can have a memorable trekking experience with clouds in the company. need off rider jeep and Kolukumala trekking also famous in this area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'munnar', '2020-05-06 07:28:04', '2020-05-06 11:28:04'),
(8, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Manaali', 'image/destinations/manaali1896355733.jpeg', 'March', 'September', 2, 10, 'Kullu Manaali Airport', 'Kalka–Shimla Railway', 'Himachal Pradesh is a northern Indian state in the Himalayas. It\'s home to scenic mountain towns and resorts such as Dalhousie. Host to the Dalai Lama, Himachal Pradesh has a strong Tibetan presence. This is reflected in its Buddhist temples and monasteries, as well as its vibrant Tibetan New Year celebrations. The region is also well known for its trekking, climbing and skiing areas', '', '<h2><strong>Rohtang Pass</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ottd87_y12g/maxresdefault.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rohtang Pass, is a high mountain pass on the eastern Pir Panjal Range of the Himalayas around 51 km from Manali. It connects the Kullu Valley with the Lahaul and Spiti Valleys of Himachal Pradesh, India</p>', '<h2><strong>Vintage Hotel</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://r1imghtlak.mmtcdn.com/ka9a0insbt5h9e6pvlc45nrs001d.jpg?interpolation=progressive-bicubic&amp;downsize=700:360&amp;output-quality=50\" style=\"height:411px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Book&nbsp;<em>Hotel Vintage hotel Manali</em>&nbsp;online at Yatra.com,&nbsp;<em>hotel</em>&nbsp;room price OFF on&nbsp;<em>Manali hotels</em>. See&nbsp;<em>hotels</em>&nbsp;reviews, location, address, photos, contact details with free cancellation &amp; instant confirmation.</p>', '<h2><strong>Snow Valley Resorts, Manali</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://t-ec.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max1280x900/105/105845290.jpg\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Book&nbsp;<em>Snow Valley Resorts</em>&nbsp;hotel&nbsp;<em>Manali</em>&nbsp;online at Yatra.com Best Deals &amp; Offers on&nbsp;<em>Manali</em>&nbsp;hotels. See hotels reviews, location, address, photos, contact details with free cancellation &amp; instant confirmation.</p>', NULL, '<p><strong>By Road :</strong>Manali is very well-connected to important tourist destinations like Leh, Shimla, Kullu, Dharamshala and New Delhi by means of a network of state-run as well as private buses. The bus journey from Delhi to Manali is 550 kilometres, and it is advisable to book your tickets in the air-conditioned Volvo coaches, as the buses are more comfortable than ordinary ones, keeping in mind the long distance of the journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail :</strong>Daily buses ply from Delhi, Chandigarh and Dehradun for&nbsp;<strong>Manali</strong>. One, who is planning to&nbsp;<strong>reach Manali by train</strong>, may find the narrow gauge track up to Jogindernagar that is the closest railhead to&nbsp;<strong>Manali</strong>. The approximate drive from Jogindernagar to&nbsp;<strong>Manali</strong>&nbsp;is 3-4 hours en route Mandi and Bhuntar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air :</strong>The nearest airport is at Bhuntar, located approximately 50 kilometres away from Manali. Domestic flights connect Bhuntar with Delhi and Chandigarh. Once at the airport, you can take a pre-paid taxi to Manali. However, owing to weather conditions, flights are not the most reliable option for getting to or out of Manali.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'manaali-1', '2018-04-30 03:17:34', '2018-04-30 03:17:34'),
(9, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'Pangong Tso', 'image/destinations/pangong-tso1023343613.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 3, 6, 'Kushok Bakula Rimpochee Airport', 'Srinagar Railway Station', 'Pangong Tso, Tibetan for \"high grassland lake\", also referred to as Pangong Lake, is an endorheic lake in the Himalayas situated at a height of about 4,350 m. It is 134 km long and extends from India to China. Approximately 60% of the length of the lake lies in China. The lake is 5 km wide at its broadest point. All together it covers 604 km². During winter the lake freezes completely, despite being saline water. It is not a part of Indus river basin area and geographically a separate land locked river basin. The lake is in the process of being identified under the Ramsar Convention as a wetland of international importance. This will be the first trans-boundary wetland in South Asia under the convention.', NULL, '<h2><strong>Night stay in camps near Pangong Lake</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s-ec.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max1024x768/116/116022093.jpg\" style=\"height:506px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do campfire and barbecue. Homestay option is also available here. But i would recommend a camp stay, specially near Pangong lake, it has its own charm.</p>', '<h2><strong>The Ladakh Camp</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mountaintrails.in/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/rsz_adventures.jpg\" style=\"height:391px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Been a part of travel industry for the last 15 years, we felt the lack and necessity of accommodation at different locations around Ladakh and thus we came up with the idea of setting up deluxe tented camps under the umbrella of &ldquo;<em>Ladakh Camps</em>&nbsp;and Retreats&rdquo;. Located in three different areas, Pangong, Tsomoriri and Nubra</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>By Road :</strong>Pangong Tso can be reached after a a five-hour drive from Leh. From Leh, one passes through the Changla Pass and then through Tangste. There are regular bus services run by state road transport corportation (J&amp;KSRTC). Taxis can be hired from Leh to the Pangong Lake. Motorbikes, cars and jeeps are also available at reasonable rates. Make sure to fill fuel at Leh and also carry extra fuel, as there are no petrol stations near Pangong Tso.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail :</strong>Kalka is the nearest railway station to Leh. Buses or taxis can be hired to reach Manali via Shimla. There are regular taxis and bus services from Manali to Leh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air :</strong>Leh is well connected with other important places in India. Regular flights link Leh with Delhi, Jammu and Srinagar.</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p>There is no particular &ldquo;best time to visit&rdquo; Pangong Lake. It all depends on what you are interested in. If you love being in the company of snow, then winters (November to February) is the best time to visit the lake. During this time, however, Pangong Lake remains completely frozen and you can enjoy walking on its frozen surface, as well as ice-skating. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'pangong-tso', '2018-10-04 10:26:13', '2018-10-04 14:26:13');
