(17, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'Zanskar', 'image/destinations/zanskar610108383.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 1, 10, 'Zanskar Airport', 'Jammu Tawi Railway station', 'The second branch is formed by two main tributaries known as Kargyag river, with its source near the Shingo La (5,091 m) (16,703 ft), and Tsarap river, with its source near the Baralacha-La. These two rivers unite below the village of Purney to form the Lungnak river (also known as the Lingti or Tsarap river). The Lungnak river then flows north-westwards along a narrow gorge towards Zanskar\'s central valley (known locally as jung-khor), where it unites with the Doda river to form the Zanskar river.', '<p>Zanskar is a high altitude semi-desert lying on the Northern flank of the Great Himalayan Range. This mountain range acts as a climatic barrier protecting Ladakh and Zanskar from most of the monsoon, resulting in a pleasantly warm and dry climate in the summer. Rain and snowfall during this period are scarce, although recent decades have shown a trend towards increasing precipitation. Several water-driven mills were built during ancient periods of drought at a great distance from the villages, but have been abandoned because running water is now available nearer to the settlements. Zanskari houses, though otherwise well built, are not adapted to the recently increasing rainfall, as their roofs leak, catching their surprised inhabitants unprepared. Most of the precipitation occurs as snowfall during the harsh and extremely long winter period. These winter snowfalls are of vital importance, since they feed the glaciers which melt in the summer and provide most of the irrigation water. Parts of Zanskar valley are considered some of the coldest continually inhabited places in the world.</p>', NULL, '<p><strong>Ratna Hotel Ladak</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://thumbnails.trvl-media.com/D50JsGTu520D7o3mVkW5wQF75hc=/773x530/smart/filters:quality(60)/images.trvl-media.com/hotels/23000000/22580000/22574100/22574019/445ffbd2_z.jpg\" style=\"height:549px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inaugurated on 27th June 2014, &quot;RATNA HOTEL LADAKH&quot; welcomes you with typical ladakhi homelike hospitality in an oasis of peace and tranquillity. Located only 8Km East from the busy center of Leh Town, our guests can retreat comfortably to this calm and beautiful place amid a local rural setting on the banks of the Indus river. Our roof top terrace offers an unmatched panorama view on Indus Valley and the surrounding mountain ranges</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>By road&nbsp;</strong>:It is noteworthy that the road that links Zanskar with Kargil is open from mid July to early November. Buses. Jeeps, gypsies and taxis are easily available for transport to Zanskar from Kargil. Kargil is approximately 235 km away from Zanskar. During the months of June and July you may trek into Zanskar from Panikhar or Parkachik onwards.</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p>Owing to the altitudes the Zanskar valley is accessible only during the summer months. The winter months are too harsh for travel in Zanskar. It is noteworthy that in the winter months the water of the River Zanskar freezes and becomes the Chador road.</p>', NULL, 'zanskar', '2018-07-16 07:20:51', '2018-07-16 01:50:51'),
(18, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Delhi', 'image/destinations/delhi1206786277.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 2, 3, 'Indira Gandhi International Airport (16 km)', 'New Delhi Station (4 km)', 'Delhi the capital land of India. Delhi has been the ruling seat of several dynasties and seen many revolutions and cultural impacts. The city is home to some prominent buildings like the Supreme Court, The parliament, the Rashtrapati Bhavan and more since it is the administrative center of the nation. Yet, on the other hand, you will find great ancient monuments. Build from as early as the initial eons of the Mughal\r\nera narrating tales from the bygone years. So, come fall in love with Delhi. Anyone who visits Delhi will immediately notice how the ancient heritage of the city lives side by side with the everyday hustle and bustle of a modern metropolis.', '<p>Do u have packed your bag for A Trip To Delhi? Here&#39;s our best list of the most wondering things to do in Delhi, the great &ldquo;capital land of India&rdquo;<br />\r\nThings to do in Delhi are plentiful and varied. We have drawn up a best exhaustive list of thrilling activities that will help you experience the mindblowing beauty and charm of this great, historic city. Delhi is the confluence of the ancient and the modern, of centuries-old heritage and modern glitz.</p>', '<h2><strong>Mughal Gardens</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hlimg.com/images/stories/738X538/mughal-garden-delhi_1521001248m.jpg\" style=\"height:494px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Delhi having plenty of things to explore and enjoy, from Mughal gardens to Delhi University campus, from historical monuments to crowded shopping malls. Delhi has a plethora of things for tourists to do, and it is up to you to pick and choose which items you want to tick off your list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Monuments and Architectural</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://static2.tripoto.com/media/filter/nl/img/1/SpotDocument/1478499366_1461066911_india_gate.jpg\" style=\"height:449px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Several dynasties ruled over the Delhi Sultanate sequentially, the remaining signatures are still standing with its proud symbols There are many instilling monuments like the Humayun&rsquo;s Tomb, Red Fort, and the Qutub Minar; all of which are UNESCO heritage centers. There are also beautiful architectural structures like the lotus temple, Akshardham, India Gate and more. Don&#39;t forget the National Museum, the National Gallery of Modern Art (NGMA), the trippy dollts museum, rail Bhawan, planetarium... one could go on for a while.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Chandni Chowk</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://holidaysgenius.com/media/uploads/2016/09/Chandani-Chowk.jpg\" style=\"height:488px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its not only a shopping center but also a national historic center which speaking many stories of the Delhi. the market id of the oldest and biggest in the nation, you will notice buildings from the 17th century still being used as shops which done with few renovations. This market offers a wide variety of things ranging from clothes to spices to traditional food. The Chor Bazaar in the near vicinity also caters to the antique lovers.</p>', '<h2><strong>Mughalai Cuisine</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/0b/ff/2c/8e/amazing-place-to-be-at.jpg\" style=\"height:599px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Delhi is blessed with a number of cuisines.The street food and its Mughalai cuisine are the best ones you can experience in Delhi. If it&#39;s a Sunday, we recommend the biryani in Bijoli Grill. The Paranthe Wali Gali houses shops selling fresh exotic paranthas with intriguing ingredients. The flavors from Delhi is mindblowing. Follow it up with lassi or rabdi. For good digestion, stuff a meetha paan into your mouth. Connaught Place and Hauz Khas house some of Delhi&#39;s finest pubs and clubs to jazz up your nightlife with an ale of your choice and some music on the house. Later in the evening, head to Dilli Haat for exploring cuisines from all around India. Else, the momos and fruit beer are a mandate for the evening snackers.</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>By Air:</strong><br />\r\nDelhi is easy to access from all the part of the country and from all major international airports and most of the domestic airport. Though make sure you have arranged for suitable visa permits. Once in the city, the Delhi Metro will keep you fairly connected to the NCR region. The Indira Gandhi Airport is an important Terminal for both domestic and International travelers. You will find it easy to hire prepaid cabs or you can, once again use the metro services to get to your destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road:</strong><br />\r\nThe capital state is a well-connected road with international standard. Delhi has about 5 National Highways connecting it to major parts of north India in every direction. The NH1 links it to Punjab, the NH 2 to Kolkata. NH 8 to Mumbai, NH10 to Punjab and NH 24 to Uttar&nbsp; Pradesh. Besides buses operate from all major cities pour into Delhi&rsquo;s Inter-State Bus Terminal (ISBT) at Kashmere Gate.<br />\r\n<strong>By Train:</strong><br />\r\nDelhi is well connected with the rail network. Delhi has five major Railway Stations (Old Delhi, New Delhi station, Anand Vihar Terminal, Nizamuddin Station and Sarai Rohilla). One is bound to find trains to almost all cities from Delhi.</p>', '<h2><strong>Tibetan Market</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hilltaxi.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Tibetan-Market.jpg\" style=\"height:532px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best shopping center in India, the capital land provide all kind of stuff with best in class price. You can buy the dress materials,leather items, and handicraft products. Delhi is famous for its flea markets that are either seasonal or open throughout the year. A few of them are the Tibetan Market in CP, Sarojini Nagar Market, and Dilli Haat which are famous for their handicrafts, colorful and relatively cheap clothing among other things.</p>', NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ak.jogurucdn.com/media/image/p17/place-2013-08-05-18-b61e8220b19700e2d41782b60d280330.jpg\" style=\"height:510px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Delhi comes alive with a display of the season&#39;s blossoms and the colors of the Holi festival splash every corner of the city. However, the worst of modernity comes glaring in the summers with the intense heat merged menacingly with dust and pollution. We suggest heading to Delhi anytime from September to March to make the most of your time here. Delhi experiences a hot summer from April to July and a cold winter between December to February. But the city sure is special during winters. It&#39;s foggy and groggy but with the pleasant sun, afternoons are the perfect occasion for peeling some succulent oranges and gossiping over tea and peanuts. The haze gives way to a vibrant Spring when the central Lutyens.</p>', '<h2><strong>Experience An Off-Beat Historical Tour</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://swantours.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/qutub-minar.jpg?w=636\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.culturalindia.net/iliimages/Humayuns-Tomb-ili-48-img-1.jpg\" style=\"height:531px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Delhi is packed with jewels of monuments. Delhi is a place that has been a seemed to several ages of history and is a gem trove for history buffs. The most popular attractions are quite obviously the Red Fort, Qutab Minar, Humayun&rsquo;s Tomb, Jama Masjid, and Old Fort. Those all the spots cant described by sentence, it must be experienced one.Adjacent to the Qutab complex lies the Mehrauli Archaeological Park spread over 200 acres and consisting of over 100 historically significant monuments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Explore Delhi&rsquo;s Urbanised &lsquo;Villages&rsquo;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Hauz Khas Village is the beating heart of creative India. Hauz Khas, originally a residential enclave of south Delhi. This village with its medieval roots is now a bustling tourist cum commercial village with numerous art galleries, exclusive boutiques, and restaurants. Cultural activities like open-air theatre, folk-dance, and heritage walks are immensely popular among locals and visitors alike. Commercial ventures aside, Hauz Khas is also host to eco-tourism initiatives like the Deer Park (a beautifully landscaped park, home to several species like the spotted deer, peacock etc.) and the Eco Night Bazaar (selling place of organic farm produce). ShahpurJat and Lado Sarai are also interesting examples of such modernized &lsquo;villages&rsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Lotus Temple</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.indiatravelspot.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/680scale/lotous1.jpg\" style=\"height:556px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;An excellent meditation center with controls 27 marble petals that form clusters to look like a lotus. No religious script is allowed inside the temple. No lectures, sermons or spiritual meetings are allowed inside the temple. Instruments conduct musical prayers from time to time. There are nine openings to the temple in regards to the nine anatomical openings of a human body. Lotus temple preaches Baha I Faith, a concept that includes all religions of the world as one. A person of any religion or creed can visit the temple and take part in the rituals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>T Memorials Mahatma Gandhi&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://im.rediff.com/news/2014/sep/30modi-gandhi1.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; We can see the footprints of the great Mahatma Gandhi. A simple square platform of black marble marks the spot where Mahatma Gandhi was cremated following his assassination in 1948. It&nbsp;&nbsp;is surrounded by a beautiful park with labeled trees planted by notables like Queen Elizabeth II, USA President Eisenhower, Ho Chi Minh and various others. Two museums dedicated to Gandhiji are nearby. Gandhi Smriti formerly known as Birla House or Birla Bhavan is a museum dedicated to Mahatma Gandhi, The &#39;Martyr&#39;s Column&#39; at the Gandhi Smriti is the spot where Gandhi was assassinated.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Qutab Minar</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://swantours.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/qutub-minar.jpg?w=636\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Qutab Minar is an elevated, 73 m-high tower of victory, its built-in 1193 by Qutab- ud-din Aibak quickly after the victory. A 7 m-high iron pillar fixed in the courtyard of the mosque. A myth is behind the pillar is that, if you can encircle it with your hands while standing with your back to it your wish will be fulfilled. The tower has five distinct stories, each spotted by a projecting balcony and tapers from a 15 m diameter at the base to just 2.5 m at the top. The first three stories are made of red sandstone; the fourth and fifth stories are of marble and sandstone. At the foot of the tower is the Quwwat-ul-Islam Mosque, the first mosque to be built in India. An inscription over its eastern gate provocatively informs that it was built with material obtained from demolishing &#39;27 Hindu temples&#39;</p>', 'delhi', '2018-10-10 11:00:55', '2018-10-10 15:00:55'),
(19, 'Goa', 'Goa', 'image/destinations/goa430810602.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 3, 5, 'Dabolim International Airport (26 km)', 'Madgaon Station (35 km)', NULL, '<p>Well known as India&rsquo;s Party Capital, Goa gives varied pics to the mind. From its romantic beaches to its casinos, from the loud neon-night clubs to the mortal crumblings remains of Portuguese settlements, from its vibrant markets to its mind-blowing fine dine restaurants to its lovely romantic candlelight dinners, Goa is a mixed book of experiences with something more for everyone. The North Goa is the hive of thrilling activities with its numerous bars, vibrant markets, countless upscale restaurants, thrilling water sports and, life tends to slow down in South Goa. Here you can find the Caribbean type white sand beaches with coconut trees and premium resorts and hotels. Yet again the<br />\r\nUNESCO heritage areas of Old Goa will lead you to the Mediterranean. It&rsquo;s done with the colonial architecture with Portuguese churches will<br />\r\ntake you back to the old Portuguese India of 16th century.</p>', '<h2><strong>Beaches and Shacks</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.airtheworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cidade-de-goa-beach-resort-goa-exterior-view7.jpg\" style=\"height:485px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beaches are the best in Goa, you can With a large number of beaches in Goa, With en number of water spot activity</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://climateage.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/calangute-beach-goa.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goa is a small ground which well connected to all of India via air, rail and roads. Being a great destination with tourists group to the state from all parts of the world, the roadways and transport systems are well maintained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong>: The Dabolim International airport has daily flights from all important megalopolises in India. All major domestic carriers have numerous daily flights, more than that it also caters to international flights with over 90% of chartered flights in India landing at Dabolim. Among international carriers, Oman Air Air Asia, Ethiopian Airlines, Singapore Airlines, Etihad Airways, etc. have regular flights to Goa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong>: this is one of the most scenic train routes in India, it is a joyful and a lifetime experience to travel from Mumbai to Goa via<br />\r\ntrain. The vast network of the Indian Railways connects Goa to most major metros in India like New Delhi, Chennai, Kolkata,<br />\r\nKochi, Mumbai, Bangalore, etc. The trains will usually take you to Madgaon in South Goa, and you can also choose to alight at<br />\r\nThivim in North Goa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong>: Many private operators operate buses from Goa to nearby states of Karnataka, Kerala, Maharashtra, and Tamil Nadu. However, the busiest route would be from Mumbai to Goa and Pune to Goa. students and young adults flock to the state all year round to explore the party capital. Overnight buses ply daily from Mumbai, Chennai, Pune Bengaluru etc. State-run buses also exist but are not that much convenient. These buses can be booked at Kadamba Bus Terminus in Goa. If you&rsquo;re driving to Goa, NH4A, NH17B, NH17, NH17A, and NH748 are the highways. The bike axies are also available for local transportation.</p>', NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.indiamarks.com/wp-content/uploads/best_time_to_visit_Coco-Beach.jpg\" style=\"height:606px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goa blessed with warm summers. The pleasant winters are the best time to visit, Goa also having a distinct monsoon season. The<br />\r\nbest time to visit Goa is from mid-October to mid-February. The temperatures are pleasant and the weather is pretty good for enjoying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you wish to avoid wet months and enjoy the various water sports, avoid the monsoon of June to early September</p>', '<h2><strong>Get a Black Henna tattoo</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://content3.jdmagicbox.com/comp/goa/a1/0832px832.x832.161226190853.z1a1/catalogue/om-shankar-tattoo-studio-candolim-goa-tattoo-artists-lyobs.jpeg\" style=\"height:851px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can see en number of tattoo artists on the beach, you can Get a black henna tattoo just like painted onto any part of the body by a tribal tattoo artist right on the beach. Its ranging from simple to really intricate and You can choose from a large variety of designs. The most beautiful part of a henna tattoo is that it fades away after a couple of weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Visit Old Goa</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://blog.thomascook.in/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Basilica-of-Bom-Jesus.jpg\" style=\"height:602px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can found en number of attractions in the old Goa. Visiting&nbsp;Old Goa is quite the wonderful experience and one feels fully<br />\r\ntransported back in time wandering around its lanes. The Basilica&nbsp;of Bom Jesus located in Old Goa. Its a UNESCO World Heritage site. It contains the tomb and mortal remains of St Francis Xavier. A must visit for first-timers!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Go on a Cruise</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://img-aws.ehowcdn.com/877x500p/s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/contentlab.studiod/getty/4f38d5403a8447d398ee029baf277df5\" style=\"height:456px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get on board one of the Sunset/ Casino Moonlight/ cruises onthe Mandovi River. They&#39;re great entertainment! The yachts are<br />\r\ntotally lit up at night and look like glittering jewels floating downthe Mandovi. Make sure to carry your lucky charm if you are in the mood to wager!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Saturday Night Market (Arpora)</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://drbenjaminhabib.files.wordpress.com/2011/05/imgp0086-hippie-woman-hula-hooping-at-ingos.jpg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Saturday night market shows cultural influences from all across the world. You can walk through the shop and meandering<br />\r\npaths .you will get all the things from homemade knick-knacks to handicrafts spices, teas, and, leather products and designer<br />\r\njewelry. This is only functioning during the high tourist season (October &ndash; April) from 4 pm to 11 pm. There are also a lot of<br />\r\noptions to drink and eat and a bit of live music on offer as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Celebrate Christmas in Goa</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn3.blovcdn.com/bloglovin/aHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZibG9nbG92aW4tdXNlci1pbWFnZXMtcHJvZC5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGdXNlci1pbWFnZS0yNzg0NDEwMS0xNTEwODEyNTIxLTVhMGQyYjY5ZTJlOTE=?checksum=95a430a39d74a08b2344839d97a14d025d634523&amp;format=j\" style=\"height:536px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goa has got the cutest Christmas culture in all of India! Goa illuminates up like a bulb during X&rsquo;mas time. Every path have<br />\r\ndozens of carols and lanterns can be heard in every nook and cranny of the state. All The religion of Goa celebrating this event<br />\r\nwith an optimum level of happiness. There is lots of drinking, feasting, and merry-making and the whole state has a wonderful<br />\r\ncharm to it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Dolphin Watching</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://img.rezdy.com/PRODUCT_IMAGE/22810/00_whales_lg.jpg\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dolphin spotting is in season between the months of October to May. Most dolphin spotting boat cruises start from near the point<br />\r\nof the Mandovi River. Dolphin spotting trips usually start early in the morning and you can use the service of a professional guide.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Indulge in Water Sports</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.insider.gr/sites/default/files/metanasteusi.jpg\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the popular &amp; fun things to do in Goa, you can enjoy the water bikes banana ride, paragliding etc. The Calangute beach is the hub of water sports activity. And all the main beaches are interconnected in a walkable distance</p>', 'goa', '2018-07-30 07:29:27', '2018-07-30 01:59:27'),
(20, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'image/destinations/himachal-pradesh326103452.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 5, 15, 'Shimla Airport (Jubberhatti)', 'Kalka Railway Station', NULL, '<p>India&rsquo;s prominent hill station in India, with a lot of enthusiastic wonders. Varying from cold and snowy Alpine mountains to lush<br />\r\ngreen sub-tropic valleys. You can enjoy and explore a lot of adventurous activities in the valleys. Himachal is the hub to many<br />\r\npicture sque hill stations. You can treat your eyes on enchanting colonial style architecture that crafts the landscape of Shimla,<br />\r\nexperience a heightened sense of spirituality at Dharamsala or go skiing and trekking in Kullu and Manali. Here is everything you will<br />\r\nneed to know to plan a trip to this Himalayan Paradise.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://images.adventures.is/assets/uploads/2017/05/18135404/rafting-gullfoss-canyon-iceland47-1200x800.jpg\" style=\"height:533px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Himachal is the action hub of northern India. Depending on where you are,</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Trekking:</strong>&nbsp;One of the best and most popular activities in Himachal is just walking! Keep walking for happy feet in valleys So, just tie your&nbsp; trekking shoes on, gear up to camp for a night under the clear blanket of stars and make sure you get a local along with you.you can also take a small tent along with you. If you are a beginner, then we suggest you go around for short half day or day treks and get to know the mountains a bit more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Explore the Waterfalls and Adventure Sports:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Jana falls situated at Naggar, a village near Manali is surrounded by deodar trees, which gives an enchanting view of&nbsp; apple&nbsp; orchards,clustered rocks and views of snow-capped mountains. here is the Bagsunag fall, popular for it religious significance. The&nbsp; Rahala&nbsp; waterfalls lay on the way to Leh is a pristine site to behold. Plan a day picnic by one such waterfall to make the most of your vacation. You cant miss the most adventure camping in Himachal, For camping, you can either go to Dalhousie, Kullu-Manali, Solan, Chail, or Dharamshala. For those looking for some mountaineering and rock climbing, head to Reo Purgyil, Jorkanden, Shilla or Rangrik Rank and the ones who want to slide down the snow-laden mountains can go to Shimla. There is a bit of everything for everyone in Himachal.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tripcrafters.com/images/articles/slides/4831-1505560116.jpg\" style=\"height:446px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air:</strong> Three domestic airports situated in Himachal Pradesh.The Kullu-Manali Airport is a gateway to the northern side of the state, like Manali, Spiti etc. The Kangra Airport at Gaggal is closest to Dalhousie and Dharamsala. The Shimla Airport is the southernmost airport, but services to this airport are not regular.Flight services are available from most Indian cities including Delhi, Mumbai,Chandigarh,etc.The flight schedule is frequently varying as per the climatic condition.<br />\r\n<strong>By Rail: </strong>The Kalka railway station is as far as you can go in this hilly State. Its the starting point of the UNESCO World Heritage Site Kalka&ndash;Shimla Railway, the narrow gauge toy-train up to Shimla and enjoy the scenic beauty that the hill-station has to offer.<br />\r\n<strong>By Road:</strong>&nbsp;Road transportation is the important way of transport in this state. The well maintained and good roads that wind around the hillsThey connect every city within the state and also connect Kashmir and Chandigarh through roads that are on every biker&rsquo;s wish list. Parts of Himachal Pradesh are also connected to Delhi and Haryana.You will find a number of buses and taxis scouting&nbsp;these routes .Frequent buses are available from Delhi to Shimla. It will take an overnight journey from Delhi to Shimla.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.indianholiday.com/pictures/travelguide/things/gallery/235_1834.jpg\" style=\"height:599px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You have a lot of things to fill your bag in Himachal, the shopping in Himachal gives a different experience. Almost every town in Himachal has markets lined with shops selling all kinds of souvenirs like woolen shawls, jewelry, handwoven wall hangings, wind chimes, sculptures, antique objects, prayer flags and pretty much anything that you will want. The popular shopping destinations are Kotwali Bazaar and&nbsp; Jogibara Road market in Dharamsala, Manu Market in Manali and Lakkar Bazaar and the Mall Road in Shimla.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.homevilas.com/images/city/Kangra.jpg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Kangra is known for madhra, a savory dish of chickpeas prepared in a different of spices. Among the non-veg foods, chha gosht is a popular dish that has a lamb marinated and cooked in spicy gravy. If you happen to explore Himachal during the festive time then you will be enticed by the aroma of freshly baked akotri, a special cake made Himachal Pradesh is a great place to enjoy the &lsquo;Pahari&rsquo; (of the&nbsp; mountain) cuisine. A popular snack among the Himachali folk is the babru, a version of kachoris served with yummy tamarind chutney. Dham from the northern districts consist of a full meal consisting of fresh red kidney beans and green lentils served with rice and curd.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://d27k8xmh3cuzik.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Adventure-Activities-in-Solang-Valley-Manali.jpg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The climate highly depends on where you are and at what peak your destination point lies.The state experiences three seasons - a&nbsp;long rainy season, a chilly winter and a warm summer .Summer here is usually regarded as the tourist season as the weather is quite pleasant in most parts of the state. The state is bustling with activity around this time of the year.While valley regions can get a little hot, the hill-stations like Shimla and Manali offer an escape from the hot plains of the country. Snow is common in the winters in Kullu, Manali and other northern cities.if you want to enjoy the snow,November to February is the best time.In the southern cities like Shimla and Dharamsala, winters are quiet but not as cold as the northern cities.</p>', '<h2><strong>Manali</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hlimg.com/images/places2see/738X538/manali%20cover%20image_1472295446p.jpg\" style=\"height:536px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Well known as Lover&#39;s Paradise and India is Honeymoon capital&quot;,Manali offers the enchanting cuteness of lush green meadows and tall coniferous trees. The misty climate provides some respite from the overall raw heat of the North Indian summer and adds to the charm of the place. It&rsquo;s the hub of Adventure sports like paragliding, skiing, trekking and mountain biking are common among the snow- capped slopes and mountains. A few attractions of Kullu Manali include The Great Himalayan National Park, Brighu Lake, Bijli Mahadev Temple and the celebration of the Dusshera Festival.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Shimla</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://static.dnaindia.com/sites/default/files/styles/full/public/2017/07/08/591290-530859-shimla-pti.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Situated at a height of 2200 m, Shimla is one of the most eminent tourist destinations in the country. Set amidst beautiful hills and mystical woods, Shimla is one of most aesthetically planned cities in India. Retaining the aura of its erstwhile position as the summer capital of the British Raj, Shimla offers beautiful colonial architecture including quaint iron lamp-posts and Victorian and neo-gothic structures. &quot;Mall Road&quot;, which is the main commercial strip of Shimla offers plenty of scope for shopping and is dotted with tiny, quaint eateries. There are some beautiful Picnic spots around Shimla, and one can also go on some lovely walks in and around town.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Kulu</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.vivekanandatravelspltd.com/uploads/packagesgallery/KULU%20VALLEY.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Kullu is known as one of the most popular tourist spots in Himachal Pradesh. Kullu is also popular as a sister town to Manali which is on much higher altitude and provides more scenic views. .Situated at an altitude of 1230 meters, Kullu is a nature lovers paradise. Abundant with lush greenery, pristine river streams, and a wonderful climate, Typically travelers cover both Kullu and Manali in one trip. Tourists coming to Kullu and Manali can indulge in a lot of adventure sports activities like river rafting, trekking, mountaineering etc. Ullu also has few important temples like the Raghunath Temple and Jagannathi Devi Temple. Apart from temples, the Pandoh Dam and Chandrakhani Pass are also must-visits in this region. Kullu is also&nbsp;used as the base town to reach&Ecirc;Manikaran, Kasol, Malana, Bhunter&nbsp;and Rohtang Pass too.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Rohtang Pass</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://images.financialexpress.com/2017/05/rohtang.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The pass is located at a massive height of 3978 meters, the way up the hills is a thrilling experience and a treat to the eyes. This is the famous, spectacular road that connects the elusive Leh-Ladakh region with the rest of the country. It is a 51 kilometer stretch from Manali to Leh, and many travelers come here to revel in the pure beauty of the pass itself! Each year the pass is open from June to October. As the vehicle climbs higher on the Manali- Keylong road, the beauty of the landscape around will leave you awestruck. It is easy to lose yourself in the serenity of the glaciers, the bubbling of the Chandra River and the pure expanse of white snowfields surrounding the highway. A peculiar fact behind the name of the place is that it was named so because a number of people working in CBRE died whilst trying to cross this treacherous stretch.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Kasauli</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://allseasonsz.com/Images/DestinationPage/hamirpur-important-lakes.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Located about 77kms away from Shimla, Kasauli too has retained the cobble-stone beauty of the British Raj. Nestled amidst beautiful woody forests of pine and cedar trees, Kasauli owes its mystical and serene ambiance to the lavish Victorian buildings built by the Britishers who resided here years back. Kasauli is a small town in the south-west part of Himachal and is on the relatively lower edges of Himalayas. The beauty of this quiet little place is reinforced by its avenues of Himalayan Oaks, Chir Pines, Horse Chestnut trees and&nbsp;the odd Juniper, which run along the edges of the two main roads.&nbsp;Kausali is dotted with magnificent little cottages, neatly trimmed&nbsp;gardens, and lovely fruit orchards. An Arts Centre has been set up at&nbsp;Ivy Cottage by the nephew of the celebrated Indian artist Amrita&nbsp;Shergill. You can also find wool of the finest quality if you visit some of the Tibetan stalls that are found here.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Dalhousie</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://c1.hiqcdn.com/customcdn/1024x768/uploadimages/travel/Dalhousie-11750_1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Dalhousie, one of the best among most tourists visiting Himachal Pradesh is well known for its enchanting natural beauty and its old world charm. A hill station of the Dhauladhar Range, nestled against the banks of the Ravi River, Dalhousie offers adventure enthusiasts the thrill of some great treks and white waters for rafting. This hill station was one of the most favorite summer destinations of the ruling Britishers and this is indeed reflected in the majestic Victorian style mansions in this region The prime attraction here is the Jandhri Ghat, a palace shrouded by tall pine trees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Dharamsala</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.villaparadiso.in/home-img/slider-3.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Dharmasthala meaning the Land of Charity is a beautiful blend of heritage, culture, and religion. Dharamsala is famed as the holy residence of the Dalai Lama and houses the Tibetan monk in exile. Dharmasthala situated Around 17kms from the Kangra Valley with&nbsp;the Dhauladhar range as a backdrop, Tall regal conifers, hefty oaks, and a caressing, salubrious atmosphere make Dharamsala an ideal getaway for nature lovers, and people looking for some introspection and alone time. The lower division is the Dharamsala town itself whereas the upper division is popularly known as Mcleodganj. Here, you can tour the Kangra Art Museum, War Memorial, and the Kunal Pathri Temple.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Kufri</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://1913578542.rsc.cdn77.org/pictures/travel_guide/attractions/skiing-in-kufri-head-440.jpeg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Just 13 km from the ever famous Shimla, the panoramic views, and temples after a bit of trekking are worth the time. Kufri itself is mostly treated as a spot for the tourists visiting Shimla and it is advisable to club sightseeing in Shimla or nearby areas like Chail, Mashobra, Naldehra or Narkanda as well if you intend to visit Kufri. Also, Kufri is a relatively crowded and popular attraction as almost everyone visiting Shimla comes here. Kufri is situated at an altitude of 9000 feet, Kufri is a tiny, chilly hill station in the state of Himachal Pradesh. It is famous for hiking, skiing, beautiful scenery, and fantastic weather. The best time to visit is from April to June. The skiing season peaks between November and February. Kufri is also well known for its breathtaking panoramas of the Himalayas.</p>', 'himachal-pradesh', '2018-10-10 10:57:41', '2018-10-10 14:57:41'),
(21, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'image/destinations/jammu-and-kashmir334216462.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 5, 10, 'Sheikh Ul Alam Airport (0 km)', 'Jammu Tawi Railway Station (0 km)', NULL, '<p>Jammu and Kashmir is well Known as &lsquo;Paradise on Earth&rsquo;. Jammu and Kashmir is one of Indias most romantic tourist destinations and it has a prominent place in Indian tourism map. The state is popular for its scenic beauty, is situated in the palm of Himalayan territory. A lot of cultural diversity to be explored here, The state is a religious amalgamation with natives practicing Islam, Buddhism, and Hinduism. Here you can enjoy vales, snow, mountains etc</p>', '<h2><strong>Shikara Ride</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tripcrafters.com/images/articles/slides/4686-1505801146.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ride provide beautiful glimpses of Srinagar.your trip is incomplete without a shikhara ride on the waters of Dal and Nagin Lakes. The rides can be availed from 6 am to 5 pm all days of the week. The price may vary from 150 INR to 250 INR per person. You have to bargain in a perfect way.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Adventure sports</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.ctidoma.cz/sites/default/files/images/sjezdovka.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to get thrilled? do some extraordinary adventure things ? the state has numerous adventure sports to excite you. Some of these include skiing, paragliding, river rafting, mountaineering etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Visit Buddhist Monasteries</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.clicksandtales.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Leh-City-Entry-Gate-Ladakh.jpg?resize=660%2C496\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can visit the old and legendary monasteries of Buddhist. Ladakh is predominantly a Buddhist region. If you are seeking spirituality and want to escape to from the hustle and bustle of the chaotic city life, a visit to a monastery is a must. Located 20 km away from Leh, Thiksey<br />\r\nMonastery is the largest in Ladakh and is iconic for the various Shakyamuni Buddha statues in it. Some other popular monasteries are Stok, Spituk, Dikshit and Likir monastery.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/simplotel/image/upload/x_0,y_342,w_3648,h_2052,r_0,c_crop,q_60,fl_progressive/w_960,f_auto,c_fit/the-universal-tours/Jammu_Kashmir_Tour_The_Universal_Tours_2_anqqdq\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air:</strong> The state has three airports with regular flights from all major cities of India. You can fly to Sheikh Ul Alam Airport in Srinagar, the Jammu Airport in Jammu or the Kushook Bakula Rimpochee Airport in Leh depending upon you are the destination. The area is a military Hubs so photography is not allowed inside the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail:</strong> Jammu is good in the rail network, you can get down at either Udhampur, Jammu Tawi, or Banihal railway station depends on your route. The Jammu Tawi station, situated in Jammu is well- connected to other major cities in India. Udhampur railway station is also in the Jammu region. The Banihal railway station is situated in Ramban district and has rail connectivity to Srinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road:</strong> If you are traveling by road, You can enjoy the longest road tunnel in the country on the way to Jammu to Srinagar. You can go via National Highway 1A as it connects to different cities of Jammu and Kashmir. You can also avail government-owned buses as well as travel in a four-wheeler. There are good and cost-effective private buses operating in neighboring cities like Manali, Shimla, Ludhiana, and Delhi.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/thetalesofatraveler.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Kashmir-Art-and-Crafts-11-e1514815705453.jpg?resize=1024%2C683\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Jammu and Kashmir best for a traveler who having purchasing habit, the state can be considered as a shopper&rsquo;s paradise. .Kashmiri shawls and carpets are a must in your shopping list. especially the Pashmina wool shawls.The saffron from Kashmir is the best in the world. The dry fruits available in the markets here are of the best quality in India. Handicrafts are also a popular shopping item here and there is an entire string of government handicraft emporiums in Srinagar. The floating market in dhal lake will give a different kind of shopping experience.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://flavorverse.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Jammu-and-Kashmir-Foods.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Kashmiri cuisine is a heartwarming experience for foodies especially ] The rich flavors and taste in, Jammu is the best foodie paradise for non-vegetarians. &lsquo;Rogan josh&rsquo; and &lsquo;yakhni&rsquo; are the most popular mutton dishes And don&#39;t forget the mouth-watering Kashmiri cuisine&nbsp; Wazwan whereas &lsquo;vegetarians can enjoy dum Olav&#39; (made with potatoes). Don&rsquo;t forget to try the street food served in this state; the most recommended ones being &lsquo;kaladi kulcha&rsquo; and &lsquo;gul gule&rsquo;.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tripcrafters.com/images/articles/slides/4729-1503752201.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jammu is the winter capital of The state, whereas Srinagar is the summer capital. if you want to enjoy the snow, winter months of October to March are the right time to explore the Srinagar area, and you can also enjoy the Jammu region at that time. The summer months from April to October are best to visit the Kashmir region to enjoy the valley view of Kashmir. It&#39;s best to avoid the hot months of May and June. March and April is the spring season and early summers in the Kashmir valley and it&rsquo;s the time of saffron cultivation it will give a different experience to your eyes - the hills are lush green and flowers blossom all around, making this a beautiful and vibrant time.</p>', '<h2><strong>Sightseeing Around Jammu</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://d3r8gwkgo0io6y.cloudfront.net/upload/K0/Dal-lake-Shikara-kesari-tours.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;You can explore many attractions in Kashmir, the summer capital of the state. Visit the oldest mosque in Kashmir, the Khanqah-e-Moula, created as early as 1395 AD. Standing right opposite the Khanqah, on the left bank of the Jhelum river, is Naev Masheed (also known as Pathar Masjid). This unique mosque which is architecturally different from the other mosques of the region. The mosque was built by Emperor Jehangir&#39;s wife, Noor Jehan during the early 17th century.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Sking and Vales</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://memorableindia.com/images/uploads/images/ice-skating-in-gulmarg-jammu-and-kashmir-india.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The ideal places for skiing are Gulmarg, Pahalgam and Thajiwas glacier in Sonamarg. These are the valleys which giving a&nbsp;picturesque view of nature. if you like a high adrenaline rush and adventure sports, you should not miss out on going skiing on your trip to Jammu and Kashmir. Skiing is only possible in the winter time and else you can enjoy the beauty of vales.its all the destinations are packed with viewpoints. There is exclusive government owned accommodations for skiers at Patnitop, Gulmarg, and Sanasar.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Mountaineering</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.apherald.com/ImageStore/images/lifestyle/57/hiking-647x450.jpg\" style=\"height:350px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A close encounter with the snow-clad hills and passes is a must on your trip. The state beckons hoards of mountaineering enthusiasts every year. You can enjoy the thrill at its optimum level. Some of the well- known peaks for Mountaineers are Nun-Kun of Zanskar Ranges, Gulap Kangri, and Kang Yatsey.</p>', 'jammu-and-kashmir', '2018-10-04 10:35:25', '2018-10-04 14:35:25');
