(22, 'Karnataka', 'Karnataka', 'image/destinations/karnataka451017715.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 5, 10, 'Banglore', 'Banglore and Mangalapuram', NULL, NULL, '<h2><strong>Enjoy the monuments</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-ab32de762e84a8859fc802dd6d52695f\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Karnataka is the best place to explore the architectural beauty. The Historical Monuments in Karnataka are among the most beautiful and evocative monuments in India. The ancient monuments in Karnataka rank prime among the manifold tourist attractions of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Explore the nature and wildlife</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/b9/01/c4/b901c4fc876db5e028fc0183c9169f38.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can explore a different kind of natural beauty from this state like beaches in Gokarna, India&rsquo;s largest waterfalls in Jog, and the thick forest and wildlife sanctuary etc.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.keralatravelplanner.in/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/how-to_reach-kerala-620x330.jpg\" style=\"height:426px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By air:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Karnataka has 6 airports to your easy access Kempegowda International Airport located in Bangalore the capital state of Karnataka. The airport is quoted as the third busiest airport after Delhi and Mumbai. It is associated with numerous flights with perpetual flights for London, Dubai, Hong Kong, Mauritius along with the domestic flights for Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Goa, Nagpur and much more. There are tons of places to travel and accommodations to stay near the airport. These are historical as well as amusing places; Devanahalli Fort, Tipus Birthplace, XtremeZone Paintball, Esteem Mall, The Venugopalaswamy Temple are some examples. You can hire an online taxi and prepaid taxi from the airport itself. Mangalore international airport located in the coastal city of Mangalore. The airport is located about 13 kilometers northeast of the city, near Bhajpe. So its also known as Bhajpe airport. It is the second international airport homed in Karnataka. It?s just 16 kilometers from the central railway station making your travel fast and mobile.its operate to GCC countries and major megapolises of India<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Hubballi international Airport is situated on Gokul Road, 8 Kilometer west of Hubli. It is well connected with the railway, as the nearest railways station is just 8 Kilometers away. The 369-acre airport serves the twin cities Hubli and Dharwad. The place has its fair share of tourist attractions, with a decent accessibility. Other major domestic airports are, Mysore Airport, Belgaum Airport, Jindal Vijaynagar Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By rail:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Karnataka having two main railway hub for easy access to the state. Mangalore and Banglore. Mangalore railway station is well connected with the major north Indian states and it&rsquo;s the main junction of Indian Railway. Banglore airport well connected with and Andhra Pradesh ,Tamilnadu and North and western side of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By road :</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Roads are the central connectivity of the state. The highways are international standard and all the destination in the state is correctly connected. There are 14 national highways and 114 state highways with total length of 28,311 km.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.spectrahut.com/media/wysiwyg/kashmir-handicrafts-02-1200x800.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can fill your bag with en number of products, the land is famous for its handicraft product. Mysore is the shopping hub of traveler. You can get Mysore sandal and soap which one is best in the class of the world, also the commercial streets of Banglore will make wonder you like anything.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/article17071272.ece/alternates/FREE_660/21bgbhu-Karunad+GNE15D4RA.3.jpg.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The land provides a different kind of taste in the different area. Cusine of theland will treat you with a great taste. Coastal Karnataka dishes like ottekadabu with red chutney and mango chutney, Mangalore&rsquo;s neer dosa and buns with kurma and chutney</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://besttimetovisitjogfalls.files.wordpress.com/2013/05/besttimetovisitjogfalls.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Karnataka blessed with a different climatic condition of its diverse terrain. The average temperature in Karnataka resides on the warmer side as same as other states of south India. Winter season is the prominent time to visit the state, you can enjoy the pleasing weather across the state. The peak season for Karnataka travel is from October to March covering the post-monsoon and winter seasons. The brief winter period does not result in harsh cold weather making it the ideal time to visit Karnataka.</p>', '<h2><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.visiit.com/uatres/images/package/PK00000612/atmalinga-temple.jpg\" style=\"height:525px; width:800px\" />Bangalore - Gardens City</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.photographylife.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/BKC_3118a.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangalore is the capital Karnataka state. The city having a lot of nicknames like Silicon Valley of India, Pub Capital of India, Air Conditioned City, and City of Gardens. All the names are apt for the town because of the climatic condition cultural condition. Bangalore has acquired the tag of student city and has also emerged as the software hub of the country. It is a young, vibrant city offering all modern amenities like malls, pubs, theatres, cafes, galleries etc. it also blessed with gardens and forts. Nandi hills are one of the best hideout place of young vibes</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Mysore</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://1913578542.rsc.cdn77.org/pictures/travel_guide/mysore-697.jpeg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>well known as the Palace City of India, it has a prominent place in the tourism map of India. Mysore is the second largest city in the state of Karnataka. Situated at the base of the Chamundi Hills, with Mysore Palace being one of the most visited monuments. From botanical and zoological gardens to temples, st.philomina church and palaces in Srirangapatanam, Mysore has lots to offer. Located around 143 kilometers away from Bangalore, it is easily accessible by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Mangalore</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.trawell.in/admin/images/upload/932329593StMarysIsland_Main.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mangalore is a popular maritime city of Karnataka. Located en route from Kerala to Goa, The meandering streets lined with coconut trees, the breathtaking beaches, terracotta-tiled roofed houses, some remarkable churches and temples and spicy food allows its guests a moment of much- needed tranquillity. The land is near to the destinations like Mookambika, Jog falls, Udupi etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Hampi</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.thenewsminute.com/sites/default/files/styles/news_detail/public/Hampi_750x500.jpg?itok=xHEBl93q\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the destinations are world&rsquo;s famous heritage sites, make you wonder by their utter magnificence. its one of the famous heritage circuit of south India Hampi is once the capital of the Vijaynagar Empire that ruled the Deccan between 14th and 16th century A.D. Hampi even in its ruins today, is majestic, charismatic and alluring. Towering over the extraordinary landscape that greets the eyes, the group of monuments and temples at Hampi. Also, the Tungabhadra Dam giving a spectacular view to your eyes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Aihole &amp; Pattadackal</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://jwalanam.in/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/jw-ai.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.trawell.in/images/itinerary/Pattadakal1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The balance of the Chalukyan dynasty at Badami, Aihole, and Pattadakal boasts of some of the perfect specimens of temple architecture. Those dominate the architectural style in South India. The groups of temples are exquisite views of craftsmanship and living testimonies of the perseverance of the artists.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Bijapur</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://1913578542.rsc.cdn77.org/pictures/travel_guide/bijapur-688.jpeg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bijapur boasts of some magnifying monuments of Islamic style which blossomed during the reign of the Bahmani Sultanates which lasted between 15th and 17th centuries. The most famous is the Gol Gumbaz which has the largest dome in the world after St. Peter&rsquo;s Basilica in Rome.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Belur &amp; Halebeedu</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mekanagadde.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ChennaKeshava-Temple-Belur-1194x597.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-s25Jw62r_H0/VPkzpEslHvI/AAAAAAAAIZg/W0tQFYbLpd8/s1600/Belur17.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halebeedu and Belur are the home to some of the best examples of Hoysala architecture. The temple architectural beauty is one of the&nbsp; promising&nbsp; examples of Indian architecture. The immeasurable beauty and sheer excellence of workmanship that marks the architecture of this period have survived centuries. The intricate carvings of the Chennakesava temple at Belur provide mindblowing experience to the voyager.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Shravanabelagola</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.indianholiday.com/pictures/travelguide/other-images/dest_head_img-279.jpeg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 57 feet tall monolithic statue of Gommateshvara located here is the world&rsquo;s tallest monolithic stone statue. Shravanabelagola is a Jain pilgrimage destination of much repute.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Coorg</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.explara.com/103430457301803203543379194201990491543749n20160427151509.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coorg is also known as Kudak stuff dreams are made of. coorg is hedonist&rsquo;s paradise with a mesmerizing landscape, mouth-watering food, hot coffee. Its closeness to the Abbey Falls, Dubare Elephant Camp, and Rajiv Gandhi National Park makes it impossible to give Coorg a miss. This picturesque hill station located 256 kilometers from Bangalore town</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Gokarna</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gokarna is their dream destination. With its alluring white open beaches and clear blue sea, Gokarna is hard to resist. Sitting on a cliff watching the sun setting on the sea leaves a lingering impression. The malpe is very near to Gokarna.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Malpe beach</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://enkalna.com/wp-content/uploads/job-manager-uploads/main_image/2017/08/IMG_4385.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Malpe beach is having two attractions the calm and quiet beach and the mindblowing island which gives the picturesque view of nature, Udupi temple is very near to the beach.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Murdeshwar</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://images.thrillophilia.com/image/upload/s--ie3jjIjU--/c_fill,f_auto,fl_strip_profile,h_800,q_auto,w_1300/v1/images/photos/000/051/304/original/Lord_Shiva_statue_at_Murudeshwara.jpg.jpg?1458198447\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murdeshwar is a temple town of Lord Shiva. Famous for the biggest Shiva statue in India and the beach with the statue is giving a treat to your eyes.</p>', 'karnataka', '2018-10-10 11:20:26', '2018-10-10 15:20:26'),
(23, 'Tamil Nadu', 'Tamil Nadu', 'image/destinations/tamil-nadu1716251048.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 5, 10, 'Chennai', 'Chennai', 'If you wish to explore and enjoy the true serenity then visiting TamilNadu is the best. The hillock like Nilgiris mountain ranges providing a\r\nromantic picturesque view. Tamil nadu is the popular destination for pilgrimage tours, travelers and wayfarers have begun to explore other\r\nparts of this untouched state. The tranquil nature of this lush green state is a great blessing to India.', NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://blog.myhappyjourney.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Pay-a-visit-to-numerous-ancient-temples.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The state is home to staggering 33,000 temples several of which are designated World Heritage Sites by UNESCO. Ancient culture greets you here at every turn of your head. You can enjoy the cultural vibe and natural richness in a full-fledged manner. TamilNadu divers in the lifestyle and Tamil pronunciation in a different manner. You can enjoy the Waterfalls, hill stations, pilgrim centers. So TamilNadu is a well-packed bag for an extraordinary traveler. Enjoy the art forms like&nbsp; Bharathanatya, which originated in Tanjore district in Tamil Nadu and also you can enjoy a Karagattam is a Tamil folk dance involving the balancing of clay or metal pots or other objects on the dancers head.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.tourmyindia.com/states/tamilnadu/images/how-to-reach-tamilnadu.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The state of Tamil Nadu has a well-developed and maintaining transportation system that provides road, rail, and air connectivity to all parts of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;By Air:</strong> TamilNadu is well connected with air routes and the state having six airports, four international and two domestic Chennai International Airport situated in the city of Chennai in Tamil Nadu. The airport has daily flights from all important megalopolises in India. It is the 4th busiest airport in India and 47th busiest airport in Asia. The airport controls more than 400 aircraft movements in a day. The airport also has a metro station which easies to connects the passengers to various parts of Chennai city. Coimbatore International Airport is located at Peelamedu, about 13 km from the city center, its operates to several states and also good in an international network. Madurai International Airport which located about 12 km from Madurai railway station. A city bus service is available for passengers from the airport along with car rental counters. Tiruchirappalli International Airport is Serving Tiruchi in the state of Tamil Nadu, This is located on the Tiruchirappalli and Pudukkottai National Highway. It is about 5 km from the city center. The airport covers an area of 702 acres. The Bus Stand in Tiruchirapally is about 13 kilometers from the Airport Tuticorin Airport serves the districts of Tuticorin and Tirunelveli in southern Tamil Nadu. Salem Airport is located in Kamalapuram, 15 kilometers north-west of Salem in Tamil&nbsp; Nadu. Both are domestic terminals Bangalore is well connected from Salem Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;By Rail:</strong> The train route in Tamil Nadu extends over a large area. Headquartered in the capital city Chennai, the Southern Railway covers a wide area in Tamil Nadu. Chennai Central is the central railway station in Tamil Nadu for trains departing north. The Nilgiris Mountain Railway, one of the UNESCO World Heritage Sites in Tamil Nadu, connects the hill station of Ooty to Mettupalayam near Coimbatore city. whereas Chennai Egmore station serves as a hub for trains leaving south. Other major railway stations in TamilNadu are as follows Madurai, Tiruchirappalli, Salem, Katpadi, and Coimbatore Junction. Chennai is also running a suburban railway network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;By Road:</strong> TamilNadu had a well-maintained road network. Road transport in Tamil Nadu is maintained by Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation (TSTC) and State Express Transport Corporation. National Highway 47, NH 49, NH 208, and NH 220 run from Tamil Nadu into Kerala. NH 67, NH 207, and NH 209 connect Tamil Nadu with Karnataka. NH 205, NH 219, and NH 234 connect the state with Andhra Pradesh. The scenic East Coast Road (ECR) runs between Chennai to Cuddalore via Pondicherry. The bank of roads of the rural area shows the real picture of the customs and lifestyle of TamilNadu There are regular buses, both government and private, operating between significant tourist destinations in Tamil Nadu. Chennai, Madurai, and Coimbatore have an extensive road network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-ViP20Rxcq5w/U2QzRN9yviI/AAAAAAAABY4/0jcbwAOJ2I8/s1600/World\'s_Most_Crowded_Place_Ranganathan_Street_T.Nagar_Madras_Tamil_Nadu_Saravana_Stores_India.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hill stations are popular for its shopping outlets, Astrophysical Observatory, and filter coffee. You can get the clothes and dress material at a good price. Kanchipuram sari which also known as&nbsp; Kanjivaram sari is a sari that&#39;s traditionally woven by weavers from<br />\r\nKanchipuram. These saris are known for their intricate designs, the material, and color pattern. The dolls are known as &#39;thalayatti bommai and the famous Thanjavur paintings also attract your showcases. These products will make the memories more colorful.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://imgcld.yatra.com/ytimages/image/upload/t_seo_Hotel_w_930_h_550_c_fill_g_auto_q_40_f_jpg/v1422961653/Domestic%20Hotels/Hotels_Coimbatore/Hotel%20Tamilnadu%20(TTDC)/Overview.jpg\" style=\"height:473px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; You can Enjoy Different taste in the different part of the state, Think of Tamil Nadus food and what mostly comes to mind is filter coffee, idli- vadai, and dosai. You can enjoy the fish from Hogenakal. Chettinad chicken curry and its masala from Karakudi. will make water in your mouth. The different types of breakfast dishes you can enjoy from the state.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://d27k8xmh3cuzik.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Kodaikanal1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different parts of Tamil nadu can experience different weather conditions because of its diverse terrain, In the summers it can get bit<br />\r\nhot and humid climate, but you can visit the hill stations on that time and it will be pleasing rather than other parts The accurate time to visit Tamil Nadu is from October mid till February mid as the temperature level comes down .its the best time for sightseeing and enjoying the outdoor activities. This also good time to visit some of the great temples of Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.tamilnadutouristplaces.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/boat-ride-hogenakkal-falls.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The state is home to staggering 33,000 temples several of which are designated World Heritage Sites by UNESCO. Ancient culture greets you here at every turn of your head. You can enjoy the cultural vibe and natural richness in a full-fledged manner. Tamil Nadu divers in the lifestyle and Tamil pronunciation in a different manner. You can enjoy the Waterfalls, hill stations, pilgrim centers. So Tamil Nadu is a well-packed bag for an extraordinary traveler. Enjoy the art forms like Bharathanatya, which originated in Tanjore district in Tamil Nadu and also you can enjoy a Karagattam is a Tamil folk dance involving the balancing of clay or metal pots or other objects on the dancers head.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Golden triangle south India of Chennai-pondy-Mahabalipuram</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/20/Brihadeeswarar_Temple_view_1.JPG\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The capital city of Tamil Nadu and home to Marina beach. The prominent thing of the city is the ancient architecture and the traditional vibrancy. Chennai exudes a peaceful nature and a tranquil lifestyle. Major attractions are marina beach, crocodile park, AVM studio etc Mahabalipuram is The only place in India surrounded by the Rathas of Pandavas. All the nook and cranny of Mahabalipuram has a telltale. Mahabalipuram is also known as Mamallapuram is the most frequented hotspot of devotees. The rock monoliths are a spectacle and Mahabalipuram is home to the Shore temple. There is a history behind every stone left unturned in this land. The tremendous Dravidian architecture is the crux of attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Pondicheri</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fqABK53nPmQ/maxresdefault.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Enjoy the temples and festivals</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://im.hunt.in/cg/City-Guide/festival.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tamil Nadu has been a pilgrim&rsquo;s hotspot for ages. Travelers from across the world embark on a journey to Tamil to revel in the religious festivities. Festivals in Tamil Nadu take place throughout the year Pongal is the most important festival in Tamil Nadu. it takes place in the month of mid-January. Pongal is celebrated for more than three days All temples are significant examples of architectural beauty. The festival time for each temple is making an excellent atmosphere in the temple premises. Rameshwaram,madhurai,palani, tanjavoor are the major pilgrim hubs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Enjoy a hill station</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://iliketowastemytime.com/system/files/kodaikanal-india-hills-hd-wallpaper.jpg?download=1\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Nilgiris hills are well known for its breathtaking cuteness and serene surroundings. Ooty and Kodaikanal are the major hill stations of Tamil&nbsp; nadu, Yercard also well known for its cool atmosphere An abode of lush greenery and misty Nilgiris hills, Ooty is euphoria for travelers. The pleasant climatic conditions make Ooty a hub during summer. Ooty is visited by tourists throughout the year. Etched with tea plantations and the fragrance of eucalyptus in the air, The flower show also very famous, the Ooty Mettupalayam train travel is a lifetime experience for each traveler.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Kodaikanal Known as the most quiescent hill station in Tamil Nadu, Kodaikanal has rightfully earned its name., Kodaikanal is a secluded hill station and gives you a break from the busy city life. Known as the gift of the forest, guna caves suicide points golf club, the lake is the main destinations, take a bicycle and have around in Kodai lake in mist will be a wonderful experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Sunset and sunrise at Kanyakumari</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.yatramantra.com/kerala/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/kanyakumari-sun-set-816x544.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Its a confluence of three great oceans namely Full of wonder and a real spectacle, Kanyakumari is a jewel of the South., The Bay of Bengal, The Arabian Sea, and the Indian Ocean joining here flowing. The tip of Peninsular India, pastiche of culture, history, Kanyakumari is also famous for its trade and commerce realms. And also the great heritage and tradition. kanyakumari is also a pilgrim spot and sees a lot of cultural epics in her eyes. The sunset and sunrise in the full moon will be a treat of your eyes</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Coracle ride at Hogeneckal</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/tourist-family-coracle-ride-hogenakkal-falls-tamil-nadu-deep-canyons-though-which-cauvery-river-flows-64441455.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Known for the mindblowing waterfalls &amp; cascades situated in river Kaveri at Dharmapuri district. The river Kaveri over there forms the border between Tamilnadu and Karnataka. So, the left or the south side of the river lies in the Tamilnadu part and the North of the right side of the river Kaveri lies on the Karnataka side. The boatman will stop at a small island along the riverside. You can eat fresh fishes over there from the river Kaveri. You can chill along the river, take a good bath in the river.</p>', 'tamil-nadu', '2018-10-10 11:08:38', '2018-10-10 15:08:38'),
(24, NULL, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'image/destinations/andhra-pradesh1166305648.jpeg', NULL, NULL, 5, 10, 'Hyderabad Airport', 'Hyderabad Railway Station', 'Andhra Pradesh is well- known for its monuments, temples, natural resources, and rivers. Although the\r\nmajor language spoken here is Telugu. Andhra Pradesh Tourism has always been the frontrunner in\r\nattracting the greatest number of tourists, inland and foreign, as it boasts of a naturally, ecologically,\r\nculturally and religiously rich and diverse variety of tourist destinations that are treasures of visual treat\r\nwhere one can continuously explore new experiences of visitor gratification and delight. The beauty of the\r\nplace calls people from all across the globe throughout the year. But, there is always the best time to visit\r\nany place. On an average, the temperature remains hot and humid in the state.', NULL, '<p>Each part of the state blessed with each activity to explore for a perfect traveler. The land having plenty of&nbsp; treasures for a voyager.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Enjoy the monuments</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.trawell.in/admin/images/upload/712214319Anantapur_Main.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Andhra Pradesh is the one of the perfect place to explore the architectural beauty. The Historical Monuments like Charminar, Golconda fort are among the most beautiful and evocative monuments in India. The ancient monuments in Andhra Pradesh rank prime among the manifold tourist attractions of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Explore the nature and wildlife</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.t2india.com/Images/places/ALR/Attractions/A64_1.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can explore a different kind of natural beauty from this state. Explore the Kolleru Lake Bird Sanctuary, Araku Vally, Borra caves .. showing the richness of the natural beauty of the state Explore the architectural wonders: You can enjoy en number of the architectural symphony in Andhra Pradesh the great Tirupati temple one of the pioneering example of temple architect and its one of the best<br />\r\npilgrim center of India. The Ramoji ravu film city is another wonder of Andhra Pradesh, it&rsquo;s the biggest film city of India. birla temple also a well-known tourist spot in Andhra Pradesh</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-Va736AiquyM/UwBc_vH4imI/AAAAAAAAASY/1ajfJJLbsws/w600/kailash-giri-1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By air:</strong> Andhra Pradesh has many airports, which serves the needs of both tourists and residents commuting to different parts of its large expanse. Begumpet Airport, which also known as Hyderabad Airport, it is the major as well as the only international airport of Andhra Pradesh. Hyderabad boasts of the sixth busiest airport in India. Keeping the rush of passengers in mind. The international terminal is known as Rajiv Gandhi International Airport terminal, and domestic is known as N. T. Rama Rao Terminal. The major domestic airports are situated in Visakhapatnam, Warangal, Rajahmundry, Vijayawada, tirupati, Kadapa and Donakonda</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By rail:</strong> Andhra Pradesh is a big state and the railway&#39;s lines that cover it are extensive too. The railways network brings visitors from distant places outside the State too. The nearby states like Kerala, Tamil Nadu, Odisha, Chhattisgarh, and Maharashtra are well connected with the state. In the development of industry and tourism, the railway plays a vital role in Andhra Pradesh. There are 182 stations and Running over a stretch of 5,046 km the railway network in Andhra Pradesh is an extensive one covering the entire State. Having within itself the Eastern Ghats route, which extends from Anantagiri to Visakhapatnam the State, is known to have the highest broad gauge rail track in the whole world.<br />\r\n<strong>By road :</strong><br />\r\nThe state is well connected with the best in the class road. With easy access to buses and taxies. The extensive road system embraces three National Highways, which connects the state with all the major cities of the country. A huge network of state roads is also maintained by the local government in a good manner. In the cities and adjoining villages, auto-rickshaws serve the requirements of the local transport.<br />\r\nTourists can easily hire private taxis, ranging from the luxurious to average ones, which are available in all the towns and cities of Andhra Pradesh.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.hindustantimes.com/rf/image_size_960x540/HT/p2/2017/11/03/Pictures/_3ed23b8e-c099-11e7-9033-2159153d9ac6.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The city is as famous for its indigenous goods and pearls.You can fill your bag with en number of products, the land is famous for its street markets and bazaars.Laad Bazaar (Chudi Bazaar), Antique Market, Begum Bazaar are the best places to satisfy your purchase<br />\r\nbag.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.fastchef.in/upload/1492757226-Cover-Source-bookyourtable-byt.blogspot.com_.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Andhra Pradesh is the land for the lip-smacking aromatic biryani. Hyderabadi biriyani is known as the best biriyani in India. The mouth-watering taste of the Biriyani will stay in your mind for a long time. Peoples are traveling a lot of time for only to taste the Hyderabadi Biriyani.</p>', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.holidify.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Virabhadra-Temple-Lepakshi.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Andhra Pradesh is a big state which provides different climate condition in a different area, October to February is preferred as the accurate time to visit Andhra Pradesh. The pleasing Weather and atmosphere will be perfect for the travel. The temperature may fall somewhere around 15&deg;C. It is a perfect time for wandering around the different tourist hub of the state. In the summer is in March to may, this time The temperature reaches as high as 40&deg;C in Andhra Pradesh. Also having a small scale monsoon here its alsogood climate if the sky is clear, but we cant predict the condition of weather.</p>', '<p>Do you have packed your bag for A Trip To Andhra Pradesh? Here&#39;s our best list of the most wondering things to do in Andhra Pradesh, &ldquo;The Land of Dawnlit Mountains&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Hyderabad</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d8/Mecca_Masjid_%28Mosque%29401.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The capital city of Andhra Pradesh The city of smiles, of lights, of a thousand faces, endearingly called the Pearl City, Hyderabad offers a lot of variety of tourist attractions ranging from Heritage monuments, Lakes and Parks, Gardens and Resorts, Museums to delectable cuisine and a delightful shopping experience. The Charminar is as much the signature of Hyderabad. Mecca Masjid is A two hundred yards southwest of the Charminar is the Mecca Masjid, so named because the bricks were brought from Mecca to build the central arch. Golconda is one of the famous forts of India. The name originates from the Telugu words &ldquo;Golla Konda&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;Shepherd&rsquo;s Hill&rdquo;. Birla Planetarium is India&rsquo;s most modern planetarium and first of its kind in the country. The Salar Jung museum houses one of the biggest one-man collections of antiques of the world by Mir Yousuf Ali Khan, Salar Jung III. Excavated in 1562 A.D. Hussainsagar Lake excavated in1562 A.D. Hussain Shah Wali during the time of Ibrahim Quli Qutb Shah, the lake has a promenade that is a busy thoroughfare today.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Tirupati</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.daiwikhotels.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/tirupati-balaji-temple.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Tirupati is one of the major pilgrimage centers in India. The city is located at the southern part of Andhra Pradesh, Tirupati is situated in the Chittoor district at the foothills of the Eastern Ghats. the word Tirupati is a Tamil word as saint Ramanujacharya who was a Tamil Vaishnava saint was responsible for founding this city. The town is famous for its temple dedicated to &lsquo;Balaji&rsquo;, a form of Lord Vishnu. The temples foundation history is unknown and it was expanded over the centuries by various kingdoms and dynasties including the Chola, Pallava and the Vijaynagar Empire. The temple is one of the major pilgrimage spots in India and especially in southern India.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Vijaywada</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.trawell.in/admin/images/upload/249844182PrakasamBarriage_Main.jpg\" style=\"height:400px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Ananta_Padmanabha_Swami_Temple.jpg/1200px-Ananta_Padmanabha_Swami_Temple.jpg\" style=\"height:425px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/Badami_cave_temples_karnataka.jpg\" style=\"height:425px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; One of the important city of Vijayawada, being the third largest city of Andhra Pradesh is number 3 on this list. The city is an agriculturally rich state and has been recognized as the Global City of the future by McKinsey.<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Undavalli Caves, Mogalarajapuram Caves, Prakasam Barrage, Bhavani Island, Victoria Museum, Kondapalli Fort, Kolleru Lake, Gandhi Hill are the major tourist spot in Vijayawada.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Puttaparthi</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.indianholiday.com/pictures/weekend_getaway/gallery/119_5343.jpg\" style=\"height:425px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Puttaparthi is a well-known pilgrim center in Andhra Pradesh. The significance of Puttaparthi rose to fame due to it being one of the major religious centers of &lsquo;Sathya Sai Baba&rsquo;. The various temples and socio-cultural centers in the town attracted a majority of the tourist&nbsp; population and pilgrims.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Ramoji Film City</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://s3.india.com/travel/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/shutterstock_240738934.jpg\" style=\"height:425px; width:800px\" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Worlds largest film studio complex situated in near to Hyderabad city.Its a magical realm filled with excitement and wonderful surprises at every turn. As the world&rsquo;s largest integrated film city and Indias only thematic holiday destination with the magic of cinema, there&rsquo;s something special for you here. Spread across a sprawling 2000 acres Ramoji Film City, set up by Ramoji</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Group in 1996, is a dreamy celluloid journey. Certified by the Guinness World Records as the world&rsquo;s largest Filmstudio complex, at Ramoji Film City, a filmmaker can walk with a script and walk out with film. For the others, Ramoji Film City flung open a wonderland where 1.5 million tourists build memories every year.</p>', 'andhra-pradesh', '2018-07-18 06:17:58', '2018-07-18 00:47:58');
